title: golden punch
directions: Mix all the juices and add 1 1/2 quarts water.
Mix well.
Add ginger ale just before serving and garnish with pineapple.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread; spread bread with butter.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and set aside.
Cook sausage until brown, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Spread over bread; sprinkle cheese over top.

title: dad's pickles
directions: Put the cucumbers in tight in quart jar!
Add all ingredients. Fill quart jar with water and cover with cap.
Let stand 5 to 6 days at room temperature, then add 1/2 teaspoon white vinegar to keep crisp and refrigerate.

title: souper sausage corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan and set aside.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Half fill a 9 x 13-inch pan with lettuce. Layer the next four ingredients.
Combine the next four ingredients and pour over the greens.
Sprinkle bacon on the top.
Then sprinkle with cheese. Cover dish with foil and chill overnight or at least 8 hours.
Do not toss.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix together and microwave until hot.
Great with any kind of chip or taco chip.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In medium bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg, then milk and vanilla; beat until nearly smooth.
In small bowl, stir together 3/4 cup flour, baking powder and salt. Add to milk mixture.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Toss berries with remaining flour into batter.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rae's crawfish stew
directions: Saute all vegetables in oleo together until tender.
Add soups and let come to a boil.
Add Kitchen Bouquet, salt, pepper and water.
Let cook 15 minutes.
Then add crawfish tails and cook 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Fold all ingredients
together in large bowl.
Put Cool Whip in first,
then
condensed	milk,
cherry
pie
filling, crushed pineapple, pecans
and
marshmallows.
Stir
to
make smooth. Pour into 13
x 9-inch plastic container and freeze 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Can be made days ahead and frozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then almonds and top with potato chips.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 9 to 10.

title: beef stroganoff(serves 4)
directions: Melt butter.
Simmer all over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mornin' muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg in mixing bowl.
Stir in brown sugar, oats and yogurt-milk mixture.
Let stand while combining the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon in a separate container.
Add dry ingredients and oil to oat mixture, stirring with a spoon just enough to moisten ingredients.
Do not overbeat. Stir in raisins and coconut.
Spoon batter into paper-lined cups, filling generously and bake for 17 minutes or until toothpick stuck into the center of one comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: 24 hour slaw(olivia sander's)
directions: Mix cabbage, onion and bell pepper with sugar; set aside. Bring celery seed, salt, vinegar, dry mustard, Wesson oil and pepper to taste to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and let stand 24 hours.

title: e. t. candies
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and sugar; roll into balls, set on waxed paper.
Put toothpick in each ball and refrigerate.

title: delightful crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Add imitation crab, chopped green onion and chopped round onion.
Mix together well.
Spread on crackers and serve.

title: sherbet punch
directions: In large punch bowl, stir together concentrates and apple juice.
Stir in ginger ale.
Scoop sherbet into balls and spoon into punch.
Makes 28 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: chocolate nut bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar, baking powder and cocoa.
Sift together into mixing bowl.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add liquid to the dry ingredients and blend.
Add butter, chopped nuts and ground nuts; mix thoroughly.
Divide dough evenly between 2 greased loaf pans.
Let stand in a warm place for 30 minutes. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Turn out on a rack to cool. Let stand 24 hours before slicing.

title: heath bar coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients as for pie dough.
Set aside 1/2 cup of dry mixture for topping.
Add egg, buttermilk and soda. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mixture will be lumpy.
Crush Heath bars.
Add to dry mixture with nuts.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rice and mushrooms(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Cut up butter and put on top.
Cover casserole and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook the sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes at a full boil.
Remove from heat and add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well, then drop by spoonfuls on wax paper to cool.

title: little smokies
directions: Place smokies in boiler and set aside. Combine jelly and mustard in a separate boiler and place over low heat until thoroughly blended and melted, stirring occasionally. Pour over Little Smokes and place boiler over low heat until mixture begins to bubble. Serve hot.

title: nutty cream cheese spread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Chill 10 minutes.
Shape mixture into a 6 x 1-inch patty; lightly coat top and sides with pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: githeri(kikuyu tribe specialty)
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Stir in cabbage and fry until tender (not mushy).
Add potatoes and cooked pinto beans.
Season with salt, pepper and beef bouillon.
Serve with cornbread.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan according to package directions. Use wooden handle of spoon to poke holes in warm cake.
Spread pineapple with juice over cake; let cool.
Make pudding according to directions.
Fold in Cool Whip and frost cake.
Sprinkle coconut over top.

title: mary's poppy seed bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans. Mix all ingredients with mixer. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Pour glaze over bread while still in pan. Leave in pan 1 hour.

title: double chocolate fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix milk, chocolate chips and unsweetened chocolate.
Microwave uncovered on High for 1 minute and stir.
Microwave until chocolate is melted and mixture can be stirred smooth.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread evenly in pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
If one pan, bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
If two pans, bake for 30 minutes. Check if done with toothpick.

title: supper on a bread slice
directions: Mix together and spread on bread. Wrap in foil, but open slightly so meat browns. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Keep bread covered until serving time. Freezes well. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Put all ingredients except for the raisins, nuts and icing in a large mixing bowl.
Blend with mixer on medium speed until they are well combined.
Chill dough in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake(low-fat)
directions: Mix pudding with milk and set aside.
In an 8 x 10-inch pan, arrange crackers in a single layer.
Spread pudding over crackers. Layer in order as follows:
banana slices, lite whipped topping, strawberries, pineapple and coconut.
Chill several hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg boats
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolk and mash with mustard and relish.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix cake mixes according to box.
Add instant pudding; mix well.
Pour this on top of melted oleo.
Add peaches.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add syrup on top of sugar.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until tested done. This is good warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: homemade soup
directions: Cook stew meat and soup bones until tender.
Add your Veg-All and potatoes.
Let cook for 30 minutes.
Then add tomato sauce and sapagetta's.
You can break them up real small.
Turn heat down and let cook slow for about 35 minutes.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar; work together.
Press down in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and white syrup over hot water.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Cut into squares.

title: easy applesauce
directions: Cut washed apples coarsely; do not peel or core.
Place in heavy pan with tight fitting lid with just enough water to cover bottom and prevent scorching (add more only if necessary; apples will release juice as they cook).
Cook slowly over low heat until apples are completely soft and can be "mushed" with a spoon. Force through strainer to remove peels, seeds and cores. Applesauce will be slightly pink from peels.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Wash cranberries; boil cranberries in water with cinnamon stick 10 minutes once boiling.
Drain through sieve.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Melt butter; add flour, making a smooth paste. Add salt, milk and cayenne. Cook until thick and smooth. Add Cheddar cheese and remove from the fire. Add well beaten egg yolks. Cool mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into the previously prepared mixture. Pour into buttered baking dish and bake 20 minutes in moderate oven (or until knife inserted comes out clean) at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie cherries and juice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Drain off about half the syrup from pineapple.
Pour remaining juice and pineapple over cherries.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Evenly sprinkle with butter chunks; top with walnuts. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serve hot with ice cream or whipping cream.

title: icebox pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate until served.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, sugar, syrup and shortening together well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips together and spread on top of bars.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mash bananas well and mix thoroughly eggs and sugar.
Melt butter; add bananas.
Stir remaining dry ingredients and add banana mix.
Bake in greased 2 pound loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: pea salad
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Marinate overnight.
Just before serving, stir in 1/2 cup chopped cashews (or other nuts) and 12 slices cooked crisp bacon, crumbled.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Cook until smooth and glossy, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice, paprika and onion; mix well.
Layer broccoli and chicken into lightly buttered casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Cook ziti per package directions; drain.
Return ziti to the pot and mix well with the ricotta and enough sauce to coat.
Put half in a 9 x 13 baking dish and sprinkle with some mozzarella and more sauce.
Add the rest of the ziti and cover with the rest of the mozzarella and sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dog bone treats
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients until well blended.
Roll the dough out on a floured board.
Cut out treats with a cookie cutter shaped like a dog bone.
Microwave at 50% power for 5 to 10 minutes, turning every 2 minutes, or bake in a conventional oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until dry.
Yield:
About 3 dozen.

title: chocolate-peppermint mousse
directions: Line loaf pan with foil, then line pan with thin slices of cake. Soften gelatine in milk for 1 minute in the microwave.
Beat the cream cheese and sugar 1 minute and add gelatine.
Remove 1/2 cup and add mint flavoring and coloring to it.
Add 1 cup whipped cream.
Melt chocolate chips 2 or 3 minutes and add to the rest of the cream cheese layer and add 2 cups whipped cream.
Over the cake layer, pour the green mixture, then the chocolate layer and cover with a layer of thinly sliced cake and chill thoroughly.
To serve, slice across the layers.

title: kabobs
directions: Mix all ingredients in large dish; stir thoroughly. Refrigerate up to 3 days, stirring frequently. Skewer meat and grill over charcoal. Serves 10.

title: jan's sugar cream pie
directions: Cream sugars and butter together.
Add flour, salt and egg. Add half and half cream very slowly, blending well between each addition.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: macadamia nut pie
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, using milk.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Add 2/3 cup chopped or sliced Macadamia nuts.
Fold in 1/2 of a large container of whipped topping.
Pour into baked and cooled pie shell.
Top with remaining whipped topping and garnish by sprinkling Macadamia nuts on top.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: bruschetta
directions: Slice French bread into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on cookie sheet.
Lightly spread olive oil on each side of bread and brown at 425° for 5 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Scald, peel and chop tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients and cook until juice is thick (45 to 50 minutes).
Put in jars and seal. Process in boiling water bath 30 minutes.
Yields 5 pints (10 cups, 20 servings).

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown onions and beef together; season to taste.
Pour off grease.
Add green chilies and a little of the grated cheese. Pour thin layer of enchilada sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Roll meat in tortillas, 2 or 3 tablespoons to each one.
Place in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over top of tortillas and sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: chili cheese loaf
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain.
Add tomato sauce, onion flakes, mustard, chili powder and garlic.
Cook over medium heat 5 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally; set aside.
In large bowl, combine 2 1/4 cups flour, sugar, Mexican season, seasoned salt and yeast.
In small saucepan over low heat, heat water, milk and butter to 125° to 130°.
Stir in dry mixture.
Mix only enough of remaining 1 cup flour to make soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured surface, about 4 minutes.
Sprinkle greased baking sheet with cornmeal.
Roll dough into 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese in center of dough.
Spoon ground beef mixture over cheese. Top with rest of cheese.
Cut into 1-inch strips along side of filling.
Alternating sides, fold strips at an angle across filling; cover.
Place large shallow pan on counter and half fill with boiling water.
Place baking sheet over pan.
Cover and let dough rise 15 minutes.
Brush top with beaten egg whites and sprinkle with additional cornmeal.
Bake at 400° approximately 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 loaf.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add Crisco; cut into flour until blended.
Add water.
This recipe is enough for 15 pie crusts. Divide in portions to use as needed.
Keep in freezer.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and apples.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix with sugar mixture.
Add pecans.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients (except pie filling and sugar and cinnamon).
Mix ingredients well.
Put half of batter in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Over this pour pie filling.
Top with the rest of the batter.
Sprinkle with a little sugar and cinnamon before putting into the oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.	This can be divided into two 8 x 8 pans to make two smaller cakes.

title: orange freeze
directions: Mix condensed milk and crushed pineapple.
Add a little orange soda pop.
Mix well.
Put mixture in freezer can and finish filling can to fill line with orange soda pop.
Freeze as you would ice cream.

title: old fashion sponge candy
directions: Use a large heavy saucepan and make sure you cook this on the stove, on the lowest
setting.

title: oven fried pork chops
directions: Mix egg, soy sauce, water and seasonings in pie plate. Sprinkle crumbs on waxed paper.
Spray jelly roll pan with cooking spray.
Dip chops into egg mixture and then in bread crumbs. Arrange in single layer on pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn and bake about 20 more minutes or until done.

title: white cloud
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours until firm.
When firm, cut gelatin into 1/2-inch cubes.
Spoon whipped topping evenly into 6 dessert dishes.
Using back of spoon, spread whipped topping into bottom and sides of each dish.
Spoon gelatin cubes into center of whipped topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mexican cheeseburgers
directions: Combine shredded Cheddar cheese with mustard and diced mild green chili peppers.
Shape ground beef into 8 thin patties. Spoon cheese mixture onto, spreading to within 1/2-inch of edges. Top with remaining patties.
Seal edges.
Season with salt and pepper.
Grill or broil until done, about 5 minutes on each side. Serve on hamburger buns or rolls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: muffelatas
directions: Assemble sandwich by layering the meats and cheese.
Mix olives, onions, garlic and dressing together and pour over top layer of meat/cheese.
Put top half of bread on sandwich and slice.
(Dressing yields 3 cups or enough for 3 to 4 sandwiches.)

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Put butter and oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pancetta (in thin strips) and cook until browned (not crisp). Add wine and cook until reduced by half.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Cook pasta.

title: apple pound cake with glaze
directions: Mix sugar, Wesson oil and eggs together and beat well. Mix flour, soda, salt and vanilla flavoring; add to other mixture and beat well. Mix apples, walnuts or pecans and coconut. Add all ingredients together and mix well. Bake at 350° in greased and floured tube cake pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes or 1 hour in 9 x 13 pan.

title: lefsa
directions: Boil Russet potatoes until soft, then rice while hot.
Take 3 cups riced potatoes, don't pack just drop into cup.
Fill in air holes.

title: sunday breakfast rolls
directions: Cut dough in half and cut into 1-inch chunks.
Put half in bottom of bread pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over bread cubes.
Add nuts, if desired.
Let rise and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: diet dippin' dippers
directions: Blend 30 seconds in blender and use for dipping celery, cucumbers, carrots, etc.

title: sausage almond rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage, onion and celery until done.
Drain and pour into 3-quart covered casserole dish.
Add rice, chicken broth, almonds and soy sauce.
When ready to serve, bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy cherry cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar together.
Blend until firm.
Pour into graham cracker crust, unbaked; top with cherry pie filling.
Chill in refrigerator for about 3 hours.

title: chinese noodles
directions: Cook and drain linguine. Cut up scallions.
Mix all together. You can add or decrease oils and sauces according to taste.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Beat in eggs.
Add sour cream and corn muffin mix.
Drain whole kernel corn.
Mix with creamed corn. Add to mixture.

title: cheese 'n spinach casserole
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in large bowl, stir together cottage and Cheddar cheese, spinach and eggs; set aside.
Combine pasta with one half spaghetti sauce. Spoon half pasta mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese mixture, remaining pasta mixture and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Cover, bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey ala king
directions: Dissolve bouillon into water.
Melt butter over medium heat. Stir in flour and broth.
Add salt, pepper, mushroom soup and turkey.
Slowly add milk.
Stir in peas and carrots.
Heat until hot.
Serve over toast.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat corn oil in skillet.
Brown pork.
Add next 6 items. Bring to a boil. Simmer 10 minutes or until done.
Mix cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water. Add to pork with green pepper.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Serve over rice.

title: cor'bleu casserole
directions: Line large
dish
with	chicken
breast.
On top of the chicken place
chopped
Danish ham.
On top of this lay slices of Swiss cheese.
Spread cream of chicken soup over this.
Top this off with previously prepared Stove Top stuffing.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar, peanut butter and margarine in glass bowl or pitcher and microwave for 2 minutes. Stir a few times during cooking process.
Remove and stir until all is smooth. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch dish. Chill 30 minutes.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Place ribs in large saucepan.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes. Combine other ingredients and simmer in another saucepan for 1/2 hour.
Drain ribs, cut in portions.
Pour marinade over ribs and let soak for 30 to 45 minutes.
Broil or grill until crisp and browned.
Brush frequently as you are browning ribs.

title: book club brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt 1 cup chocolate and butter in double boiler (or heavy-duty saucepan) over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth. Remove from heat. Mix in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla. In another bowl, mix flour, sugar and baking soda. Add flour mixture to chocolate mixture a little at a time. Spread batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining chocolate and pecans. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder. Blend in Crisco with pastry blender. Mix cold water, egg and vinegar together. Add to flour mixture. Mix and shape into ball. Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: zucchini fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two greased and floured 9x5 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350°F for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: easy rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix cake as instructed on package.
Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread rhubarb over batter.
Sprinkle with sugar; pour cream over top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain off fat.
Add corn, beans, seasoning (mixed according to package directions) and picante sauce; stir until well blended.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, nutmeg and cinnamon beat well.
Mix other ingredients.
Mixture will be stiff.

title: easy pizza burgers
directions: Cook together and drain off grease.
Add 1 can Chef Boyardee pizza sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Cool 1/2 hour.
Add 4 ounces shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Place on bun halves or crackers.
Toast under broiler until heated through.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vanilla cheese cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, margarine/butter, and cream cheese; mix until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients into batter; blend well until smooth. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies start to brown.

title: oatmeal cookies(diabetic)
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and spices.
Set aside. Mix lightly beaten egg, oil, sweetener and vanilla together in mixing bowl.
Add flour mixture, oatmeal and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream the peanut butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: raisin bread
directions: Bring water to boil.
Turn out fire and add raisins.
Add butter, salt and soda; cover and let set overnight.
Add 2 cups sugar, eggs, cinnamon and flour.
Mix well and add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chesapeake bay grilled crab cakes
directions: Gently combine crabmeat with 3 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Mix together next 5 ingredients and fold into crabmeat mixture.
Form into cakes and coat with bread crumbs.
Brush grill with cooking oil and prepare for medium heat.
Arrange crab cake on grill. Grill about 3 minutes.
Turn and grill another 3 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: spinach bread
directions: Cook spinach by package directions; drain.
Combine onion and butter in glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes (until tender).
Add spinach, mushrooms, Mozzarella cheese, Cheddar cheese, Tabasco, salt and pepper; mix well.

title: spiced coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch tube pan. Combine 1/2 cup of flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and cocoa. Cut in 1/4 cup of butter until mix resembles coarse crumbs.
Set aside.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, corn, celery, onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Put in casserole dish. Top with crackers mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25
minutes or until bubbling.

title: pulled taffy
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into deep saucepan.
Cook over low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, to the hard ball stage or to 268° by candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a shallow buttered pan to cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and flour to which the soda has been added.
Add bananas, nuts and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured pan (loaf) for 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all
ingredients together and spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: escalloped oysters or scallops
directions: Shuck oysters (saving juice).
Heavily butter a 9-inch dish then spread a layer of crumbs.
Spread oysters over this then dot with 1/2 of the butter.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the pepper then spread the remaining crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter and sprinkle remaining pepper.
Pour cream over all and bake in a preheated oven at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serves 4.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at at time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and nuts to cream mixture.	Shape dough into rolls and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator until firm enough to slice. Slice 1/2 inch thick.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°. Yield:
7-8 dozen cookies.

title: chicken salad supper
directions: Cut eggs, apple and celery into uniform pieces.
Drain kidney beans, then rinse in a little hot water.
Combine all the ingredients; toss lightly.
Serve in a lettuce lined salad bowl to 6 persons.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain mixed vegetables; set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and onion; set aside.
Melt margarine.
Crush crackers and mix with margarine.
Put vegetables in casserole dish, then mayonnaise mixture, then cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish beans
directions: Brown the peppers and onions. Add the tomato soup, beans and water.
Cook the hamburger until the red disappears.
Add to mixture.
Serve over rice.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Mix the salad dressing and the sugar together.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan the lettuce, peas, onion, celery, the salad dressing. Top with the bacon bits and the shredded carrots.
Refrigerate for 8 hours before serving.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Prepare and marinate overnight.
Add radishes, onion and green pepper, if desired, awhile before serving.
A colorful and tasteful dish!

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Place peanut butter and marshmallow cream in a large bowl. Mix the peanut butter and marshmallow.
Cream together until a soft dough is formed.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a greased dish and bake at 350°.

title: mish mosh(polish spanish rice)
directions: In a Dutch oven or any large pot, simmer pepper and onion until soft.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper and brown until all pinkness is gone.
Add tomatoes and water and simmer on low heat around 2 hours.
Add mushrooms after 1 hour.
Add Minute rice after 2 hours and simmer 1/2 hour longer.
Good one pot meal.
Can also be used for stuffed peppers.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Prepare the day before.
Beat together eggs, 2 1/4 cups milk and mustard.
Smooth together 2 tablespoons milk and mushroom soup. Put ingredients in shallow baking dish in order that ingredients are listed.
Pour egg mixture over first 3 ingredients, ending with mushroom and milk to top it off.
Spread good.
Refrigerate up to 1 day before baking.
Then bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Longer baking time needed if deeper dish is used.
(I use 13 1/2 x 8 3/4-inch Pyrex.)
Spray dish with Pam.
Great dish to make Christmas Eve for Christmas morning.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve juice according to can direction.
Slice fruit thin to float in bowl.
Add soda.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Turn out on floured board; knead a few times. Pinch off or roll and cut.
Place on greased iron baker.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill well.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: dilled onion rings
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions.
Bring to a boil and pour over onion rings in a deep bowl.
Keep pushing onions down into sauce.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
Great with any kind of sandwich.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix with mixer the first 7 ingredients.
Add carrots, pineapple and any other ingredients you wish.
Bake in 350° oven for at least 1 hour.

title: party punch
directions: Combine the frozen juice with the required amount of water, following directions on the can.
Pour into punch bowl with ice cubes.
Just before serving, remove ice cubes.
Add ginger ale and scoops of sherbet.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add corn syrup and eggs, one at a time. Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° to 370°.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheese candy
directions: Melt cream cheese in double boiler.
Add sugar.
Melt margarine.
Add chopped nuts.
Put in oven and toast.
Mix all ingredients together and pour out on waxed paper.

title: neiman-marcus
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake for 6 minutes at 375°.
Makes 60 (5 dozen) cookies.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Melt chocolate in large bowl in microwave for 1 minute on Low power.
Keep repeating until melted.
Add cereal and coconut. Stir mixture, using a teaspoon.
Drop mixture on wax paper and put into the refrigerator until chocolate sets.

title: tina's fudge pudding
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in ungreased 8-inch pan.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt. Let them set for 1 hour.
Drain, but don't rinse.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the cucumbers.
Refrigerate in a tightly covered container.
The taste of these pickles will improve after 24 hours.

title: toffee squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Spread in a rectangle about 13 x 10-inches on greased baking sheet, leaving 1-inch all around edge of baking sheet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until nicely browned.
Crust will be soft.
Remove from oven.
Immediately place separated squares of chocolate on top.
Let stand until soft; spread evenly over entire surface.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut in small squares while warm.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen squares.

title: apple-cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine 2 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese and margarine; gradually beat in 1 cup sugar and almond extract. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Spread batter evenly into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In medium bowl, combine remaining flour, remaining sugar and cinnamon; gently toss with apple slices to coat well.
Arrange on top of batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean. Serves warm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar; then eggs one
at a time.
Add flavoring and flour.
Start in a cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 hour, 45 minutes.
Oven temperature may vary.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Stem strawberries and cover with sugar.
Let stand until ready to use.
Combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick. Add Jell-O.
Cool.
Dip sweetened berries out of juice into pie shell.
Cover with mixture.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spray jelly roll pan or large pizza pan with Pam.
Press rolls together and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Soften cream cheese; add mayonnaise, garlic and dill.
Spread on cooled rolls.
Top with finely chopped veggies and cheese; pressing into cream cheese.
Cut into 2-inch squares; refrigerate and serve cold.

title: twisty beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Brown beef. Drain.
Combine all ingredients except onion.
Pour half of mixture into a greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Top with half the onions. Pour remaining macaroni mixture over onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover, top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Saute the first 7 ingredients in a large kettle.
When onion is clear and very soft, add remaining ingredients.
Turn the heat way down.
Cover and simmer at least 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Then add 1/2 cup freshly chopped parsley.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken until it is completely done.
Remove all skin and debone.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Clean and cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Steam vegetables in a pan until they are tender.

title: indian curry cheese ball or dip
directions: Mix and form into a ball or use as a dip or spread.
Top with parsley or coconut if desired.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a salad bowl, toss together broccoli, raisins, and red onions.
In another bowl, whisk together white sugar, vinegar, and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli mixture and toss to coat. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Before serving, mix in sunflower seeds and crumbled bacon.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter in bowl; add vanilla and beaten eggs.
Then stir in flour and sugar; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bea's apple bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased and floured angel food or Bundt pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 or 40 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: old fashion chocolate fudge
directions: Scald milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir often.
Cook to soft ball stage and then remove from stove.
Add margarine and cool.
Beat.
Work quickly.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into jars until half full.
Then slice onions until about 2/3 full.
Finish with cucumbers.
Pack tight but don't crush.
Pour cold syrup of vinegar, spice and sugar over to cover.
Place lids on jars.
Store in the refrigerator.
These will last about 1 year in the refrigerator.
Let stand 4 or 5 days before using.
Tops do not have to seal.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skin; peel and cool.
Cut up.
Over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter until melted.
Remove from heat. Blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes. Put in 2-quart covered casserole.
Top with 2 tablespoons butter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: buttery bread dough
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine yeast and water.
Add warm milk, butter, egg, sugar, salt and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Gradually mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
On well-floured board, knead for 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic, adding flour to board as needed.
Shape dough into ball.
Place in greased bowl; turn dough over.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down dough; shape as directed in recipe.

title: no crust egg pie
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Add milk, water, butter, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Put in pie pan or glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Boil for 2 hours in water which beans are soaked.
Add all ingredients except plantain.
Add plantain after beans are soft.
Add dumplings and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix sugar, milk and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Pinch cake into pieces and add to mixture.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread cherry pie filling on top and chill.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 2-quart casserole combine first 8 ingredients and arrange evenly in dish.
Spread potatoes over top to cover meat mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, or until light brown and bubbly.

title: world's best summer dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients. Cover and chill for one hour to blend flavors. Serve with crackers and crudities. Makes about 1 2/3 cups.

title: barbecue baked potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes; rub with margarine.
Sprinkle with kosher salt and wrap in Reynolds Wrap.
Especially delicious when done on the grill outside.
Equally good done in the oven.
Time:
1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli; drain thoroughly.
Place in a casserole.
Stir together soup and shredded cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and beaten egg.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: israel chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper. Shake the chicken in this mixture and fry lightly in the 1/2 cup butter.
Put in pan or casserole.
In a saucepan, mix the orange juice, thyme, brown sugar and 1/4 cup butter. Boil for 4 minutes. Slice a layer of thin onion over the chicken and the can of ripe olives, sliced. Pour sauce over all.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Add water, if dry.
Serve with wild rice.

title: swedish browned potatoes
directions: Peel medium sized baking potatoes (1 per person).
Cut almost through crosswise (slices 1/8-inch thick).
Brush with melted butter.
Place in shallow baking dish/pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the sugar, salt and shortening. Add eggs.
Mash bananas and add. Add soda and flour.
If nuts are added, put them into batter before flour is added or save them for decoration on top.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Melt marshmallows in heated milk.
Cool.
Freeze until like mush.
Add the whipped cream and strawberries.
Continue to freeze until firm.

title: quick beer bread
directions: Mix rye flour with 1 1/2 cups white flour.
Heat beer, honey and margarine to 105° to 115°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add beer mixture, caraway seed, salt, garlic powder and 1 1/2 cups flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour mixture and enough additional white flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured board until smooth, about 4 minutes.
Shape into ball and place in greased 8-inch round pan. Grease top.
Flatten to fit pan, cover and let rise in warm place for about 45 minutes.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: carla's easy chicken
directions: Wash chicken and cut in half (8 pieces).
Place in a Pyrex dish.
Salt and pepper.
Place bay leaves on top.
Pour can of tomatoes and juice.
Pour bottle of Italian dressing over chicken. Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease. Place all ingredients in crock-pot until all cheese is melted. Stir occasionally.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot shortening.
Place one tablespoon chicken, 1 tablespoon green chilies and 2 tablespoons cheese (grated) on each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place each one into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup; spread on top of tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining onion, cheese, green chilies and hot peppers on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Do not overcook!

title: baked carrot ring
directions: Cook carrot pieces until tender.
In a blender or processor, puree the carrots until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Blend in the eggs, one at a time, then add the sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon, pepper, milk and butter.
Bake in buttered 10-cup casserole dish in 350° oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: strawberry ritz pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time (until it looks like marshmallows).
Add cracker crumbs and nuts.
Spoon into lightly greased pie plate.
Spread evenly.
Bake for 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Fold Cool Whip and strawberries together.
Spread into pie shell.
Garnish.
Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and cream cheese. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy, about 5 - 7 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Gradually add flour and beat until blended. Stir in vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Bake at 300 for 1 1/2 hours or until cake done. Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing to wire rack. Cool completely.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Break and wash green beans.
Wash and chop peppers and green tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in glass jars and pour salted water over them.
Seal jars tightly.
Store in basement for at least 6 weeks.
Ope and use when you want them.
Drain off most of water and fry in bacon drippings.

title: ice pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into lengthwise pieces.
Place about 3 stalks dill in bottom of jar.
Fill jar with sliced pickles, standing upright.
Boil all ingredients.
Cool and pour over pickles in jars.
Add 3 small red peppers to each jar before closing.

title: old-fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Blend cake mix, water, oil and eggs in mixing bowl until moistened. Pour batter in lightly greased pan and sprinkled flour. Bake. Take toothpick and insert in mixture. If toothpick comes clean, allow it to cool. If cake mix is not clean, allow it to bake five additional minutes.
Repeat until toothpick comes clean. Pour lemon flavoring in chocolate icing and blend with spoon until smooth. When cake is completely cool, frost the cake.

title: pecan pie #1
directions: In a saucepan combine corn syrup, sugar and butter.
Bring to boiling.
Boil gently uncovered 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Cool slightly.

title: "easy-mix" biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine oil and milk.
Pour all at once over flour mixture.
Mix with fork to make soft dough. Shape lightly to make a round ball.
Place on wax paper and knead lightly 10 times or until smooth.
Pat out to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with unfloured 2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: salmon supper loaf
directions: Flake salmon; reserve liquid.
Peel and chop onion and celery. Heat butter in skillet and saute onion and celery, about 10 minutes.
Combine with breadcrumbs in a large bowl.
Add salmon, reserved liquid, salt, pepper, parsley, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Beat eggs lightly and add to the mixture with the milk. Put mixture in large greased loaf pan and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: c's potato cakes
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, egg, flour, salt and pepper in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Spoon 1/4 cup potato mixture into skillet for each of 4 pancakes.
Flatten with spatula.
Cook over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown, turning over once.
Drain on paper towels.
Add additional oil, if needed.
Repeat with remaining potato mixture.
Makes up to 6 servings.

title: tuna macaroni & cheese casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni & cheese as directed on box.
Mix in remaining ingredients EXCEPT for parmesan cheese.
Pour mixture into a 1-1/2 quart microwavable serving dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on high for 2-1/2 minutes.
Stir and continue to heat for 2 to 3 minutes more, or until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: doug's microwave peanut brittle
directions: Butter a long baking sheet and set aside.
In a 1 1/2-quart glass dish, mix sugar, peanuts, Karo syrup and salt.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave again on High 4 to 5 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes until peanuts are light brown.
Add baking soda and stir well while hot.
Pour onto buttered baking sheet and allow to cool.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water until tender; do not drain. Melt margarine in another saucepan; stir in flour, salt, black pepper, cheese and milk and cook until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese sauce to potatoes and onion; stir to mix.
Sprinkle with parsley.
(If soup is too thin, add a few instant potatoes to thicken.)
Do not boil.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Add sugar and salt to warm water.
Dissolve yeast in water. Add 3 cups flour and beat until smooth, add melted shortening, egg and remaining flour or enough to make easy to handle.
Place in a large bowl free draft.
Let rise to double bulk.
Punch down in bowl, cover and place in refrigerator until needed.
Make out rolls, let rise.
Cook at 425° about 15-20 minutes.
This will stay in the refrigerator 3-4 days.

title: apple pie
directions: Place apples in unbaked pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are done.

title: herbed cheese
directions: Thoroughly mix all together in a blender and mold into any shape desired.
Cover and refrigerate at least overnight.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: pepper-onion relish
directions: Combine vegetables and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Cover again with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes; drain.

title: candied citrus peel
directions: Peel fruits.
Cut peel into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Cover with cold water in a saucepan and let come to a boil.
Drain and repeat 3 times.
Drain; add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Continue to cook until peel becomes transparent and has absorbed all the syrup.
Roll each piece in additional sugar.
Store in covered containers.
Yield: 1 to 1 1/2 cups.

title: hot peppers (canned)
directions: Clean hot peppers; pack in jars.
Boil vinegar, pickling spices and garlic cloves.
Pour heated mixture over peppers and seal tight.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cook peas as directed on package; drain.
Mix macaroni, peas, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together; pour into a hot skillet which has 2 tablespoons oil.
Bake 30 minutes at 450°.

title: night-before breakfast
directions: Saute sausage; drain.
Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Will serve 6 to 8 people.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, cocoa and buttermilk, alternating until all have been added.
Add soda.
Mix with vinegar, vanilla and butter extracts and red food coloring.
Pour into three eight-inch cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with taco mix.
Spread over layers.
Sprinkle grated cheese over layers.
Top with jalapenos and several green onion pieces.
Serve with taco chips.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Place shredded cabbage in baking dish.
Mix sugar and flour; combine with cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over cabbage.
Place bacon slices atop cabbage.
Cover dish.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover; bake a few more minutes to crisp the bacon. Makes 8 servings.

title: great-grandma's soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Stir in sugar, nuts, crackers and vanilla.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with fresh fruit. (Enough batter to fill 1 pie pan.)

title: sausage roll
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough overnight.
Prick and fry sausage with salt, pepper and crushed red pepper.
Drain on paper towel.
Place bread dough on floured board and roll out.
Sprinkle sausage over dough.
Sprinkle cheese last.
Roll and secure toothpick.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Place on cookie sheet and cook until golden brown at 350°.

title: hot cheese bread
directions: Mix together the cheese, biscuit mix and poppy seed.
Stir in the egg and milk until blended.
Then beat by hand for a minute or two.
Sprinkle with a teaspoon of poppy seed.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool for a few minutes.

title: wine making in 5 gallon crock
directions: Heat berries in water up to a boiling point only.
Cool slightly.
Put sugar into crock.
Add water to dissolve.
Add berries and stir.
Adding a small bottle of ReaLemon to elderberries when mixing will add to the flavor.
Fill crock with tap water to within about 2 1/2 to 3-inches from the top.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover with white cloth and tie down to make sure no fruit flies get to the inside.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Add Cool Whip to condensed milk.
Then stir in thawed lemonade mix and pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter. Cover and cook until tender. Remove from skillet and set aside. Drain pineapple, reserving syrup. Set pineapple aside. Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in skillet. Gradually stir in vinegar, soy sauce and reserved syrup from pineapple. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Add pineapple tidbits, green pepper, onion, cooked chicken and water chestnuts. Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Serve over hot buttered rice. Makes 4 to 6 large servings.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add at once all remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Spray large roasting pan with Pam (or grease). Toss potatoes, bacon and dressing mix together to mix. Roast at 375° for 1 1/2 hours. Stir 2 or 3 times. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Into the cooked spaghetti, stir the butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs and set aside.
In a skillet, saute the ground beef, onion and bell pepper until the vegetables are tender and the meat is browned.
Drain off the excess grease.
Stir in the tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, oregano, garlic, water and mushrooms and simmer the mixture for 15 minutes.
Line a buttered 10-inch baking dish or pie pan with the spaghetti mixture.
Ladle the meat mixture onto the spaghetti.
Bake the dish, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese over the top and continue baking for 5 minutes or until the cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Boil rice.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a full boil.
Serve hot.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook meat, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Add soup, tomato sauce and 1 cup cheese.
Stir in pasta.
Transfer to greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: low-fat blue cheese dip
directions: Blend first
3	ingredients
until
smooth.
Spoon into bowl. Cover and
chill.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Yields 3
1/2	cups. Per 3 tablespoons contains 1 g fat and 33 calories.

title: squash cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and oil.
Add vanilla, eggs and sour cream.
Measure dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Add to creamed ingredients.
Add squash.
Add nuts, if desired.
Mix well. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle small chocolate chips over top.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter. Mix with fork until resembling coarse meal. Spread half of mixture in pie shell. Combine remaining ingredients, except egg whites, in double boiler. Cook over med. heat until thick, stirring constantly. Spoon filling into peanut butter crust. Beat egg whites until stiff. Spread over filling. Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture on meringue. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Melt butter and mix with dressing mix.
Put 1/2 crumbs in casserole dish.
Add other ingredients.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix crumbs with melted butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread on bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar, then add Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture on crumbs.
Spread blueberry filling over mixture.
Add rest of cream cheese mixture on top of blueberries.
Sprinkle remaining graham cracker crumbs on top. Refrigerate.

title: fruit salad(mary chalker)
directions: Mix together. Congeal overnight.

title: double divinity
directions: Mix sugar, hot water and salt in heavy pan. Cook over high heat stirring constantly until mixture comes to a rolling boil. If sugar crystals form on side of pan, wipe off with a

damp cloth. Turn heat down and cook without stirring until temperature reaches firm ball stage (248 degrees). Slowly pour 1/2 cup of syrup over egg whites, beating constantly with mixer at medium speed. Continue cooking rest of syrup to soft crack stage (272 degrees). Pour hot syrup slowly over egg white mixture, beating constantly. Continue beating until mixture begins to lose its gloss and a small amount dropped from a spoon holds soft peaks. Add pecans all at one and stir. Pour on sprayed pan.

title: baked chicken stroganoff
directions: Poach chicken and cut into cubes. Saute mushrooms in butter until tender. Add wine and lemon juice. Cook until liquid evaporates. In a large mixing bowl, combine chicken, mushrooms, soup and sour cream. Add noodles and mix well. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Put in a 13 x 9 x 2 cake pan. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers with melted oleo; make crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring 1 cup water to boil; melt jello in it; refrigerate jello until egg white consistency.
Beat 1 cup sugar with cream cheese.
Beat Milnot until slightly stiff; add cream cheese mixture to Milnot.
Add jello to mixture; beat well.
Pour mixture over crust.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine the first four ingredients and let come to a boil. Boil one minute only.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in raw oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoon on wax paper in small sizes.

title: frosted mocha punch
directions: Dissolve coffee in water in a large bowl.
Add milk, chocolate syrup and ice cream.
Stir until blended.
Chill.
Just before serving, stir in club soda.
Makes about 5 quarts or 20 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup (undiluted), sour cream, chilies and sauteed onion. Divide mixture in half.
Place 1/12 of chicken and sauce in each tortilla.
Roll and place in greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Pour remaining sauce over stuffed tortillas.
Top generously with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: dang good pie
directions: Melt butter and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until set and brown.

title: honey without bees
directions: Heat sugar but not until brown or melted.
Add 6 cups boiling water.
Boil 10 minutes with alum.
Take from stove.
Add rose petals and clover, which have been picked apart.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Strain; pour into jars.

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Mix beef, bread, salt & onion.
Make small meat balls.
Cook in skillet until done.
In another pan add broth, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Mix well, then add pineapple, bell pepper and cherries.
Cook until sauce starts to clear.
Add meat balls and cook till sauce clears.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine egg whites, sugar and salt. Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop 1 teaspoonful onto foil-lined oven shelves; put in 350° oven.
Immediately turn off oven.
Leave overnight.
Do not open door.
Cookies will be ready the next morning.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Shape into one-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 50 balls.

title: new england brown bread
directions: Mix whole wheat flour, cornmeal, sour milk and molasses. Sift together flour, baking soda,
powder
and salt.
Stir into other ingredients
and mix well.
Add
raisins.
Pour
into
2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 2 tablespoons butter, 1 cup flour, baking powder, salt, 1/3 cup sugar, egg and milk.
Spread mixture in pan.
Put on 2 good rows (layers) of rhubarb (1-inch long cubes).
Over rhubarb, sprinkle 1 box strawberry jello.
Mix 1/2 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Crumb this on top of jello-ed rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked ziti
directions: Grease shallow 3-quart baking dish; set aside.
In heavy, medium skillet, heat 3 tablespoons oil over medium heat.
Add sausage, onion and garlic, saute 5 minutes or until onion is softened, breaking up sausage with wooden spoon.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper flakes and 4 tablespoons parsley; heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer gently 20 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Peel and cut ends off onion; insert whole cloves into onion.

title: easy and elegant steak
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil on high.
Brown meat on all sides. Drain any excess oil.
Combine soup, water and wine or broth.
Pour over steak.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Meanwhile, toss all remaining ingredients together and place on top of steak. Cover and continue to simmer until the meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Serve with rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: my favorite potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until partially cooked.
Drain and arrange in a casserole dish. Melt butter in a saucepan; add flour, mixing well.	Add milk, cream, chicken broth, and onions.
Cook, stirring until thickened. Add salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes or until lightly brown.
Sprinkle the cheese on potatoes during the last 15 minutes of cooking time.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth. Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut.
Shape into small balls. Roll in coconut; chill.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: cream of wheat cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice cooked potatoes into large mixing bowl.
Distribute cucumbers on top, then alternate endive and onions.
Sprinkle around sugar, salt and pepper.
Scald vinegar and water to boiling.
Add oil and bring to boil again.
Pour slowly over top of lettuce, onions and seasonings on top of potatoes and cucumbers.
Lightly toss.
Slice eggs on top and lightly toss until blended.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with mixer.
Add Bit 'O Brickle. Slice apples and refrigerate in pineapple juice until ready to serve.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place in casserole dish.
Cover with meat. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: soapsuds finger paint
directions: Whip the soap and water until thick and frothy with a wire whisk, eggbeater or mixer.
Even though this is easy to clean up, you'll probably want to cover the table with a plastic tablecloth. You can add food coloring or a little paint for color variety.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Add cake mix.
Mix eggs, one at a time, beating at medium speed. Add sour cream and poppy seeds. Spray bundt pan with Pam.
Add sugar as you would flour to coat pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tart and tangy baked beans
directions: Soak beans for at least 4 hours.
Place soaked beans in a kettle and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and simmer, partially covered, until tender about 1 1/2 hours.
Drain water. Saute onions in olive oil.
Add salt, chili powder, cumin and mustard and cook 10 minutes.
Add garlic and saute 5 minutes longer.
Add mixture to beans along with remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Heat oven to 350°.
Transfer beans to a deep casserole or a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Wrap spinach in paper towel and squeeze excess water.
Add Knorr dried soup mix straight out of package.
Add chopped chestnuts, mayonnaise and sour cream; mix well together. Ready to eat.
Keep refrigerated.

title: angel food delight
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Tear cake into small pieces.
Arrange evenly in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread pudding over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Carefully spread pie filling evenly over Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.
It gets better the longer it sits.

title: uncooked lemon pie
directions: Using blender or eggbeater mix lemonade and milk (slow speed). Add Cool Whip and blend until well mixed.
Spoon into pie shell. Chill several hours.
Serves 12 or more.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch or three 8-inch round layer pans.
Measure all ingredients, except frosting, into large mixer bowl.
Mix 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pans.
Bake in layer pans for 30 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly with finger.
Cool.
Frost with Sour Cream Chocolate Frosting.

title: venison mulligan
directions: Into a large casserole, put the chopped onion in the bottom of the pan.
Sprinkle the raw rice through the onions.
Slice the potatoes and put on top.
Spread the ground venison on top of the potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour the pork and beans on top of ground meat.
Pour the tomato juice over all; poke around so it soaks through to onion and rice.
Pop in oven and bake, covered, for about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mrs. brinson's white fruit cake
directions: Chop nuts and fruit into medium-size pieces.
Dredge with small amount of flour (about 1/4 cup).
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and blend well. Sift remaining flour and baking powder together; fold into egg and butter mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extract; mix well.
Add fruit and nuts, blending well.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage leaves in water for a few minutes.
Mix first 7 ingredients.
Remove leaves from water and roll meat mixture in leaves.
Place in baking dish and add kraut on top of rolls, then add can of soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini-oatmeal muffins
directions: Grease 12 (3-inch) muffin pan cups.
Preheat oven to 400°. Into large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients.
In medium bowl, with fork, beat eggs slightly; stir in zucchini and oil.
Stir mixture all at once into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. (Batter will be lumpy.)

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix in a large mixing bowl the oleo, sugar and salt.
Add 1 cup of boiling water.
Stir until oleo is melted, then cool.
Mix 1 cup of barely warm water and yeast.
Add to oleo mixture.
Mix in slightly beaten eggs.
Add in flour a little at a time and mix well.
Cover tightly in a large container and refrigerate overnight.
Push dough down and pinch off for cloverleaf rolls. Let rise 1 1/2 hours, then bake 12 minutes at 425°.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: russian dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in small bowl; stir until well blended. Chill.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: turkey wild rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Pour into oiled baking dish and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and stir well.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes until rice is tender.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Prepare grits as directed on package.
Then add the rest together in a 9 x 13-inch casserole and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Make a well in center and add in order:
oil, egg yolks, liquid and orange peel.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in another large bowl until whites form stiff peaks.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over beaten whites, gently folding with rubber spatula just until blended.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Invert on funnel to cool.
Frost.
Makes 12 to 16 servings. 290 calories per 12, 215 calories per 16 (without frosting).

title: spatzle(small dumplings)
directions: Sift flour with salt and spices.
Add eggs and water.
Beat batter until thick and smooth.
Dampen the end of a small cutting board.
Put on 3/4 cup of dough with spatula; smooth a small amount of the dough very thin.
Cut off small strips of dough into a large kettle of boiling salted water.
Dip spatula into water several times during cutting.
If dough is too thin to hold together, add a little flour.
Cook until tender, about 5 minutes. Lift out with a slotted spoon.
Drain and place in serving dish. Continue with remaining dough, adding a little fresh boiling water to kettle each time.
Serve with melted butter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple cranberry upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 baking dish in 350° oven. Sprinkle with sugar, nuts, cranberries and pineapple. Add water to reserved juice to equal the amount of liquid specified on cake mix package. Prepare as package directs. Spread over fruit. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool 5 minutes. Invert onto large serving dish.

title: brownie mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a glass oven dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chinese sweet-sour ribs
directions: Boil spareribs until tender.
Drain; place in skillet.
Mix together next 6 ingredients; pour over ribs.
Cook until thickened, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve over hot bed of rice.

title: spinach peta "spanokopeta"(greek spinach pie)
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease a 14 x 20-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Mix spinach, eggs, Greek cheese and cottage cheese together.
Place four phyllo sheets into a pan, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Spread spinach mixture evenly on fifth sheet, alternating with butter and spinach mixture, on each sheet, with the exception of the last four phyllo, which should be buttered only.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: maui mexican soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in soup pot.
Puree tomatoes and add to pot with broth, chicken, picante sauce and beans.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cut tortillas in strips and add to soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Ladle into bowls.
Top with cheese.
Tortilla strips can be fried and drained, then added to hot soup and topped with cheese.

title: pepper steak
directions: Add beef to melted butter in a skillet, sprinkle with garlic powder and cook, stirring slightly, until browned.
Remove meat; add onion and green pepper.
Saute for 2 minutes.
Return meat to skillet along with tomatoes and bouillon cube, simmer about 5 minutes.
Blend together cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Stir into meat mixture and cook just until thickened.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: cashew candies
directions: In a bowl, combine the first four ingredients; knead until smooth (mixture will be dry).
Shape into eight rolls 5 in. long x 1/2 in. in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and freeze until firm. Place the caramels in a shallow microwave safe dish; uncovered on high until melted.
Add water; stir until smooth.
Carefully dip the frozen rolls into the caramel mixture, then roll in cashews. Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut into 1/3 in. slices.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding mix and pineapple.
Blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and blend.
Refrigerate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Drain off oil.
Place potatoes in casserole bowl.
In a small bowl, mix soup, milk and water.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture over potatoes and sprinkle minced onions on top. Place browned pork chops on top of potatoes and pour remaining soup mixture on top of pork chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: In melted butter, saute onions, green pepper and pimento about 1 minute. Add seasoning and flour. Blend in milk. Stir until thick. Add potatoes and 1 cup cheese. Stir until cheese is melted. Pour into 3-quart casserole. Spread remaining cheese on top. Bake in 350° oven 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk; boil 7 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add Hershey bars (broken up) and chocolate bits; stir well.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add nuts; pour into buttered 11 x 14-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: buffet tomatoes
directions: Cut a thin slice from the top of tomatoes and scoop out seeds and pulp.
Salt shells and invert to drain for 15 minutes.
Cook spinach in salted water.
Saute onions, celery, parsley, pepper and carrots in butter until onions are brown.
Add drained spinach to vegetables.
Stir in bread crumbs, milk, eggs, salt and pepper. Pack mixture in tomatoes and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Place in buttered baking dish and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
May be prepared a day in advance.
Serves 12.
This is an excellent dish and is very pretty for a dinner party.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat the egg and add the milk.
Sift the flour, salt, sugar, baking powder and baking soda together.
To these, add the egg and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Holding your finger over the bottom of the funnel, pour some batter into the funnel.
Drop batter into the hot oil, approximately 375°, swirling it into circles, from the center out.
Make each cake about 6 inches in diameter.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on brown paper and serve.
Funnel should have 5/8-inch opening.

title: very best baked beans
directions: Cut up bacon in small pieces and fry until crisp.
Save bacon fat and measure amount needed.
Mix all ingredients together. Grease large casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
This is best when made ahead and reheated.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Clean mushrooms, separating caps and stems.
Slice half of the caps crosswise into 1/8-inch slices.
Chop stems and remaining caps.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in an enameled or stainless steel skillet and saute the sliced caps until they just turn color, about 5 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to skillet and saute chopped mushrooms and shallots until just tender, about 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place 1 cut-up chicken in baking dish.
Pour rice on top. Pour water and soups over chicken.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: goulash
directions: Cook hamburger and onions together.
Drain grease.
Cook macaroni.
Combine all ingredients and cook until heated.

title: bacon-wrapped shrimp
directions: Place bacon on rack; cover with paper towel.
Microwave on High for 1 minute; pat dry on paper towel.
Let cool slightly. Wrap 1 shrimp and 1 pepper strip in each piece of bacon; secure with wooden pick.
Place in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Repeat with remaining bacon, shrimp and bell pepper.

title: broccoli spoon bread casserole
directions: Remove stems and leaves from broccoli.
Reserve stems for florets later use. Place broccoli florets in a saucepan with 1-inch boiling salted water.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes, until just tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: lemon blueberry coffee cake
directions: Combine egg, sugar, lemon peel and milk; mix well. Stir in Bisquick mix just until moistened. Fold in blueberries. Bake in a greased 9-inch round or square pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: Make a lettuce salad as usual.
Mix all ingredients well. This makes a small serving.
May be doubled!

title: salmon stew
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in medium sized saucepan and bring to boil.
Turn heat down and simmer while preparing white sauce. Melt butter in medium frying pan over medium heat.
Stir in flour to make a paste and brown slightly.
Slowly stir in evaporated milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Add seasonings as desired.
Slowly stir white sauce into salmon mixture and heat through.

title: apple cheesecake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together, combining well; blend in flour and salt until mixture is crumbly.
Pat on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Place apples in layers in shallow baking pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: mustard dill sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; whisk until blended.
This is very good on salmon.
Serve chilled.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: sara salade
directions: Wash and dry greens.
Place 1/3 of mixed greens in a bowl. Dot with 2 tablespoons mayonnaise and 1/3 of onion slices. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar, a dash of salt and pepper, 1/3 of peas and 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat 3 times.
Do not toss.
Cover and chill at least two hours.
Crumble the bacon.
Just before serving, top with bacon and toss.
Yields 8 servings. Preparation:
15 minutes.
Chilling:
2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Mix ingredients together with hands; form into a loaf.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake halfway through cooking time, then top with barbecue sauce.
Continue cooking until done.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine with Fluff.
Mix with electric mixer.
Add juice.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: mushroom burger
directions: Place the mushroom on a plate and pour olive oil over it. Make sure that the mushroom gills are covered in oil.
Put both the hamburger and mushroom on the grill.
Grill until the hamburger is done and the mushroom is a little browner than normal.
Put the two on a bun with your favorite condiments.

title: this is great cake!
directions: Beat well and bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, 30 to 40 minutes (9 x 13-inch pan).

title: alabama chocolate-pecan jumbo christmas fudge pie
directions: Combine chocolate crumbs and 1/3 cup melted butter.
Firmly press on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cream 1/2 cup butter; add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Stir in the melted chocolate, coffee, vanilla, flour and pecans.
Pour into the prepared crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: tuna pate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can be molded into log, ring or ball.
Coat outside with parsley and/or walnuts.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook cubed zucchini with skin on in salted water until soft, about 7 minutes. Drain well.

title: nannie's keepsake biscuits
directions: Mix, adding enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead well and mold into neat, small biscuits with your hands.
Bake well and you have a good, sweet biscuit that will keep for weeks in a dry place. They are fine for a traveling lunch.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together the sugar and syrup and cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and put in microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Take out of microwave and stir in oleo and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir quickly and pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread on pretzel crust.
Then Jell-O and strawberry on top.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Any fresh fruit with Jell-O may be used, such as: peaches/peach Jell-O, orange slices/orange Jell-O, sweet cherries with cherry Jell-O, raspberries with raspberry Jell-O.

title: chocolate pepper balls
directions: Cream real well together the Crisco and sugar.
Mix liquid ingredients and add to Crisco and sugar mixture.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to other mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls and bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine first three ingredients, stirring well, then chill.
To serve, combine chilled mixture and ginger ale in a punch bowl, pouring it over a block of ice.
Garnish with fruit slices and cherries, if desired.
Punch can be frozen minus the ginger ale, to be added when ready to serve.
Yield:
2 gallons.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy.
Add sugar slowly.
Beat until stiff.
Spread over cooled pie, sealing edges. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk and ice cream together.
Add pudding.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
