Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: baked rice
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Add sugar to eggs, mixing well.
Blend flour and cocoa.
Add this mixture to eggs alternately with the oil.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and mix well. Let sit for 6 to 8 hours or overnight in refrigerator. Makes 2 cups of dip. Dip is good with raw veggies, chips or rye bread bowl.

title: microwave apple-walnut coffee cake
directions: Lightly grease bottom only of round microwavable 8 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Beat sugar, buttermilk, oil and egg in medium bowl with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except sliced apple and Walnut Topping, just until moistened.
Spread batter evenly in dish.
Microwave, uncovered, on Medium for 9 to 10 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 5 minutes, until top of cake is set but still moist.
Arrange apple slices in spoke fashion on coffee cake.
Sprinkle evenly with topping.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 to 4 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 2 minutes, until apple slices are slightly tender and toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Let stand uncovered for 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: baked swiss cheese chicken
directions: Arrange skinless, boneless chicken in shallow baking dish. Place sliced cheese on each piece of chicken.
Stir soup and water together.
Pour mix over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over soup layer.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over hot rice.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine all
ingredients except topping (crumbs and butter).
Put in casserole dish.
Mix topping.
Pour on top of potato mix and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes with foil.
Uncover and bake additional 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sugarless cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together until smooth.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Break up angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed pineapple.
Top with instant pudding.
Slice banana and place on top of pudding.
Top with light Cool Whip.
Makes 8 servings.
This is an excellent low calorie dessert.

title: butter rolls
directions: Roll out biscuits separately in flour.
After flat, place 1 1/2 teaspoons of margarine in center.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 teaspoons of sugar over margarine.
Fold biscuits and lay in bottom of baking dish.
Use remaining margarine and sugar on top of rolls in dish. Pour vanilla over rolls and milk until covered.
Bake at 350° until bubbling and thicker, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grandma's custard pie(1940)
directions: Line pie plate with pastry.
Make a fluted standing rim. Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add the flavoring.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test with knife; if it does not come out clean, bake a few minutes longer.

title: healthy choice crab dip
directions: Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasonings.
Mix well.
Then, stir in Cheddar cheese and crab.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers, bread sticks or vegetables.
Makes approximately 20 servings.
A 3 tablespoon serving equals 44 calories and less than 1 gram fat.

title: snow peas with curry filling
directions: Trim stem and remove strings from sides of each pod.
Blanch pea pods in lightly salted, boiling water 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Using a sharp knife, slit each pea pod open
along straight edge.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Toss apple slices with lemon juice to avoid discoloring.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Beat eggs with fork in a large bowl. Stir in whipping cream and butter. Gradually add sugar mixture; stir until smooth. Stir in corn. Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is golden brown and mixture is set.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of wax paper.
Pound thin to about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine flour and seasonings in bag. Add chicken breasts.
Shake to coat well. Shake off excess.
Heat butter and olive oil in a large skillet until they bubble. Saute chicken breasts, a few at a time (do not crowd), about 2 to 3 minutes on each side.

Do not overcook. Drain on paper towels. Keep warm. Drain all excess butter and oil from pan. Add 2 tablespoons unsalted butter to hot pan. Add wine (when the butter sizzles) and add 1/2 cup chicken broth.

Let boil together for 2 minutes, scraping bottom of skillet. Add lemon juice; heat briefly. Return chicken to skillet placing lemon slices on top of breasts. Sprinkle capers over chicken. Cover and keep on low heat for 5 to 10 minutes. (Add more broth for more sauce.)
Serve on platter. Sprinkle with parsley.
Excellent with rice or pasta.

title: corn flake-peanut butter treats
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil; take off at once.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Add corn flakes; mix well.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: crescent roll cheesecake
directions: Press 1 package rolls on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, ungreased.
Beat remaining ingredients; spread on top.
Press another package on top of cheese mixture, sealing perforations before placing on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost when cool.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Mix Crisco into flour and salt by hand.
Gradually add water. Mix with hand until you can form a ball and the dough is rollable.

title: date torte
directions: Put in blender and blend until smooth the warm water, butter, eggs, sugar and dates.
Add nuts and blend until nuts chop. Combine flour and soda; fold in date mixture.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Stir in Velveeta cheese.
Mix with spaghetti and turkey.
Put into greased baking dish and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Sprinkle paprika on top of the cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, coconut and nuts together.
Add beaten eggs, milk, salt and vanilla. Add margarine.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients and beat well.
For just two people, use the batter to make "batter cakes"; they are just great.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and pour into deep dish pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts (optional).

title: last-minute beef casserole
directions: Blend soups together in 2-quart casserole.
Mix in beef, onion, garlic, peas and 2 cups noodles.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Reduce power to 50 percent.
Microwave 5 minutes more.
Stir.
Sprinkle with almonds and remaining noodles and cook, uncovered, until done, 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Beat egg.
Mix flour and sugar mixture with egg and pineapple juice and stir, then add lemon juice.
Cook until thickened.
Cool and pour over bananas, apples, oranges, grapes and nuts, if desired.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter both sides of bread and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put sausage on top of bread.
Mix eggs with 1 cup milk and add salt and pepper to season.
Pour egg mixture over sausage; sprinkle cheese on top and let set overnight in refrigerator or at least 1 to 2 hours.
Cook at 350° about 30 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil until tender. Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine chicken, chopped green chiles and green salsa; add sauteed onion mixture to chicken, tossing gently.
Set aside.
Combine flour, chicken broth and half and half or cream; cook over medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add 1/2 cup cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Set aside.
Fry tortillas one at a time in remaining oil.
Dip tortillas in cheese sauce.
Place 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on each tortilla.
Roll tortillas with seam sides down.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, covered.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: tater tot beef bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray shallow baking pan with Pam. Combine oats, milk, egg, onions, 1 1/2 teaspoons seasoned salt, basil and pepper.
Mix.
Add hamburger.
Mix.
Shape into pan. Bake 15 minutes.
Drain grease.
Arrange cheese on top of meat. Arrange Tater Tots on top cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining seasoned salt.
Bake 15 more minutes or until done.
Serve in squares.
Serves 4.

title: play dough(for kids.  do not eat!)
directions: Mix and stir over medium heat.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender. Blend until banana is liquefied.

title: jackie's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a tube or loaf pan. Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar, then add egg yolks one at a time.
Add flour, soda and sour cream, mixing well.
Stir in flavorings.
Fold in egg whites. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: coke cake
directions: Beat
together eggs, soda, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add marshmallows.
Add
to
pan mixture and mix well, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple and marshmallows.
Then add Cool Whip and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients together.
(May use a blender.) Add butter.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: kolachy
directions: Mix and beat soft margarine and vanilla ice cream.
Beat in sugar, slowly add flour.
Dough will be sticky when all mixed.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll dough, little at a time, thin on flour surface.
Cut in 2 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch squares.
Put about 1/2 teaspoon of pie filling in middle.
Fold 2 corners.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken rice
directions: Mix dry soup and rice together and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix mushroom soup with water and pour 1/2 over rice. Top with chicken, lightly salted, and pour remaining soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meatball sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients into a large saucepan.
Stir and cook over low heat about 15 minutes.
Add meatballs.
Cook for an additional 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: bob's black dog chile
directions: Saute onions, butter and garlic until transparent.
Add meat; brown.
Drain excess.
Add remaining ingredients and boil.
Reduce heat and simmer partially covered one hour or until the black dog starts howling.
Top with shredded cheese if desired.

title: persimmon pudding bread
directions: Combine milk, pulp, vanilla and sugar.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into first mixture.
Fold in nuts and raisins. Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix together and leave in refrigerator.
Top with onion rings and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: french chicken
directions: Skin the chicken; arrange in a large, shallow baking dish. Mix together the soups; pour over chicken.
Garnish generously with paprika for browning and parsley flakes for color.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: champion cheesy steak sandwich
directions: Combine Velveeta, mayonnaise, milk and mustard; stir over low heat until smooth.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add meat; mix lightly until thoroughly heated.
Fill rolls with meat mixture; top with sauce.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: blond brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan; remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar; cool.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into butter-sugar mixture. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Place mixture in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: easy cookie squares
directions: Combine 1st three ingredients and mix well; this will be very stiff.
Press evenly into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Mix next 3 ingredients in large bowl with mixer.
Pour mixture over mixture in pan.
Do not stir.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar after baking.

title: squash puppies
directions: Reserve water drained from squash.
Combine all ingredients. Add squash water, if needed, for consistency.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into deep fat to form balls the size of hush puppies.
Makes 12 to 14 puppies.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Add tomatoes, beans, 3 teaspoons chili powder, onion, catsup and green pepper.
After adding all ingredients in crock-pot stir well, then turn on low and cook slowly.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes; (with gas) it takes only 35 minutes.

title: microwaved beef stew
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, toss meat with cornstarch, salt and pepper until coated.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover. Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir; reduce power to 50% (Medium) and microwave 30 to 45 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender, stirring 3 or 4 times during cooking.
Remove cover during last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix these ingredients together thoroughly.
Make into small balls (about marble size).
Bake in 350° oven on a greased cookie sheet until done.

title: 9 cloud salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip.
Mix cheese, sugar and 1 tablespoon juice. Fold all together.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage and drain.
Add mustard. Place bread in greased Pyrex dish (do not stack bread).
Spread sausage, then cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Especially good for breakfast. May be fixed the night before and refrigerated.
Ready to cook the next morning.

title: texas tornado cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients at low speed.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Boil butter, brown sugar, evaporated milk and coconut for 1 minute.
Spread over top of cake.
Serve hot.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate.
Add sugar, flour, nuts, vanilla and eggs.
Spread this in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Spread Cream Cheese Filling over chocolate mix.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle 2 cups miniature marshmallows and bake 2 minutes more.
While hot, spread with Frosting swirling into marshmallows.
Cool.
Cut in bars.
Refrigerate.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over crushed ice.
Serves 20.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons olive oil in a large deep skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Stir occasionally.
Add ground beef and ground pork broken into small pieces.
Cook until lightly brown.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat about 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: tallarine
directions: Saute onion in butter; add ground beef.
Cook until done.
Add egg noodles, tomato soup, water, Ro-Tel and chili powder or sauce. Turn fire low and cook until noodles are tender.
Then add ripe olives and corn.
Fix this on top of stove.
Place in refrigerator until ready to cook.
Put grated cheese on top and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Open oven and let set for 15 minutes.
Then eat, it's good.

title: cherry winks
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and milk; beat about 2 minutes.
Add flour; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon of mixture in crushed corn flakes and roll; place on greased cookie sheet.
Top each with 1/2 maraschino cherry.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 90 cookies.

title: cindy's lite orange julius
directions: Freeze orange/pineapple juice mix.
In blender, mix frozen juice, banana and milk; blend until smooth.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding cheese and pepper last.
Bake in greased skillet at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger, drain then add seasoning and mix.
Mix with beans, hot sauce, lettuce and cheese.
When ready to serve add the rest.

title: trifle-traditional
directions: A nice combination is fresh strawberries and strawberry jello.

title: "edible" finger paint
directions: Mix flour and 2 cups cold water in a saucepan.
Stirring constantly, bring to a simmer.
Add cornstarch to 1/4 cup cold water and stir into flour mixture.
Cook slightly until thickened. Allow to cool and then add food coloring.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook hamburger, chopped onion, green pepper, chili powder and sugar until done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs alternately with flour.
Fold in bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan at 300° to 325° for 1 hour until done.

title: shrimp jumbalia
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in bacon grease.
Add tomatoes, catsup, lemon juice, jalapeno pepper, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp cocktail and sauce(serves 6)
directions: Combine boiling water, salt, lemon juice and sweet pickle liquid or pickling spice; boil for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Remove from heat when water returns to boil.
Let stand for 2 minutes. Scoop from water to a pan of very cold water to stop the cooking (if overcooked, shrimp shrink excessively and become tough).
Peel and devein shrimp.
Reserve and cool about a quarter of the shrimp broth to be used for refrigerating peeled and deveined shrimp.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger; cook bacon.
Combine other ingredients.
Add barbecue sauce if needed to prevent being dry.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Mix sugar and flour into a large mixing bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour into 16 1/2 x 10 1/2 sheet pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: best brownies
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on box.
Add dry cake mix, batter will be very stiff.
Mix 1/2 package of chocolate chips into batter.
Put brownie mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish prepared with Pam.
Place remaining chocolate chips on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Don't overbake!
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 1/4 pound margarine in Pyrex baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour into dish with margarine.
Add one large can of fruit, as desired.
Then sprinkle sugar over the top.
Bake at 350° until crust rises to the top and turns golden brown.

title: glazed ginger carrots
directions: Cook carrots in just enough water to cover in a saucepan with a tight lid.
When carrots are tender, drain and return to pan. Add butter, brown sugar, ginger and salt.
Mix very well.
Cook over low heat, turning often for about 5 minutes.
Transfer to a heated serving dish.
Serves 12.

title: mexican cheese
directions: Layer 1/2 pound of cheese in baking dish. Mix eggs and green sauce and pour on top of first layer of cheese. Layer remaining 1/2 pound of cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with corn chips.

title: gooseberry pie
directions: Mix and let stand 15 minutes.
Line 1 (9-inch) pie pan with crust.
Add fruit mixture and cover with top crust.
Slit several spots to let steam escape.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes longer.

title: sally's shrimp dip
directions: Heat
tomato soup, cream cheese, gelatin and mayonnaise over low
heat
until
cheese
is
melted.
Then
add onions, celery, and shrimp; stir.
Remove from heat; pour into a mold and chill overnight.
Unmold and serve.

title: broccoli and noodles parmesan
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
In a 4-quart covered saucepan, over medium heat, cook broccoli until tender.
Drain in colander.
In the same saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter; cook onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in soup and tarragon. Mix well.
Add both cheeses, stirring until melted.
Stir in sour cream, broccoli and cooked noodles.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes a good dip for fresh vegetables, also.

title: festive chicken
directions: Wrap two bacon strips around each chicken breast.
Place in a shallow glass baking dish; set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, combine soy sauce and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Pour over evenly.
Cover with plastic cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Drain and reserve marinade.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is done, basting occasionally with marinade.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: bulgarian pepper casserole
directions: Place rice and water in a saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Turn the heat down as low as possible and simmer without interruption for about 40 minutes or until the rice is tender. Remove from heat; fluff with a fork and stir in lemon juice and dill.
Set aside.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan and add remaining ingredients, stirring constantly.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.

Sauce may be stored in tightly closed jar in refrigerator for 1 week. Marinate chickens 5 to 6 hours in sauce (or overnight), then barbecue over medium coals for 1 1/2 hours, turning and basting occasionally.
Makes enough sauce for 2 to 3 whole chickens.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can fried onions. Pour into 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes, onion, salt, pepper, bay leaf and sugar in saucepan for 15 minutes over low heat.
Strain tomato mixture.

title: chicken in crescent rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place about 2 tablespoons
of chicken mixture on wide end of each triangle and roll up to opposite point.
Arrange in 8 or 9-inch oven dish.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk and remaining cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour 1/2 over chicken-filled rolls.
(Reserve remaining soup mixture for sauce topping at table.)
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: cheese balls
directions: Allow
cheese and cheese food to reach room temperature. Mix well.
Add
juice, 1/2 parsley and 1/2 of nuts;
mix well. Chill until
firm
enough
to shape into ball, about 1/2 hour. Roll in parsley and nut mixture.
Makes 2 big cheese balls.

title: chicken crescent squares
directions: Combine all ingredients except crescent rolls.
Roll out crescent rolls to form 4 rectangles on floured surface.
Divide chicken in 4 and put 1/4 in the middle of each crescent roll.
Fold sides over and pinch shut.
Cook 25 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: chicken de barr
directions: Marinate chicken in eggs overnight.
Combine breadcrumbs and parsley.
Coat chicken pieces with breadcrumb mixture.
Brown in frying pan.
After browning, put chicken in greased (Pam) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a layer of mushrooms over chicken.
Next, pour 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth over all.
Cover with Muenster cheese slices (one package).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crock pot chicken
directions: Rub bottom and sides of crock pot with butter. Rinse chicken and pat dry. Season inside and out with salt and pepper. Put chicken in crock pot. Add no liquid. Put on lid and cook on low for 8 - 10 hours.

title: chocolate-nut cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Beat in egg, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to egg
mixture.
Beat in sour cream and nuts. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes. When cool frost with icing.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonful in deep fat fryer. Cook until golden brown.

title: chicken and rice
directions: *Use any or all of the vegetables, according to your taste.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk and set aside.
Beat together cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Then stir in pudding, 20 crushed Oreos and Cool Whip.
Place in plastic flowerpot.
Top with 10 crushed cookies, silk flowers and gummy worms.
You may want to line the pot with plastic wrap.

title: "the best" oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and honey.
Blend in eggs and vanilla. Stir in combined flour, cream of tartar, soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in oats, nuts, raisins, etc.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Blend sugar and shortening until creamy; add pulp and soda mix.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add flour and spices which have been added to the flour.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix well. Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: grandma's green beans
directions: Saute bacon and onions in large saucepan until bacon is crisp. Add beans; season with salt and pepper.
Cover with water.
Cover pot and simmer for 2 hours.
Add sugar and simmer 20 more minutes.

title: bacon wrapped wieners
directions: Cut bacon into thirds.
Wrap one slice bacon around each wiener.
Put toothpick through bacon to hold it.
Arrange in large baking dish, toothpick facing up.
Mix brown sugar and catsup and pour over the wieners.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
If bacon is not cooked enough, leave a little longer.

title: tomato soup
directions: Heat tomatoes and add baking soda (will fizz).
Add milk and sugar.
Stir while heating.
A tablespoon of butter or margarine may be added.
Serve with crackers.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine carrots, raisins, coconut, apples, pineapple and nuts. Mix yogurt and mayonnaise.
Blend all ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: apricot delight salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water. Then add cold water. Let jell slightly. Drain pineapple and save the juice. Add drained pineapple, mashed bananas and small marshmallows. Let jell.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in. Fold in chopped almonds, figs and raisins.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake is golden brown and cake tester comes out clean. Cool 10 to 15 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool on rack. Drizzle Burnt Sugar Syrup over cake and decorate with whole almonds.

title: good for you cookies
directions: *I have also used mashed bananas, but they spread a little flatter than with butter.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix malted milk powder, orange juice and sugar in a glass and fill with seltzer water.
Honey may be used in place of sugar. Add a dash of nutmeg on top.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast in warm water.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; mix with sugar and pineapple.
Let sit 3 hours.
Add marshmallows and whipping cream.

title: herb stuffed eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise; scoop out yolks into bowl. Set white halves aside. Mash yolks; blend in cheese spread, mayonnaise, mustard, green onions, and pimientos. Spoon into egg white halves. Chill until serving time. Makes 24 appetizers.

title: pennsylvania dutch cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers; slice paper thin into a bowl.
Sprinkle with salt; cover and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Rinse and drain cucumbers and onion in a large bowl; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream, vinegar, chives, dill seed, pepper and sugar. Just before serving, add dressing to cucumbers and toss.
If desired, arrange lettuce and tomatoes in a serving bowl and spoon cucumbers in the middle.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: homemade dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in large cooking pan and bake until lightly brown in 350° oven, approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken chalupa
directions: Cook, debone and chop the chicken.
Spray a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Line dish with chips.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Braise hamburger, onions and celery in frying pan.
Blend remaining ingredients (except noodles) in mixing bowl.
Add hamburger mixture.
Spoon into casserole.
Bake uncovered 2 hours at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut canned biscuits into thirds.
Combine sugars, cinnamon and melted margarine.
Dip each piece of biscuit in melted mixture and place in a Bundt or tube cake pan.
Pour rest of mixture over top. Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool; invert pan.
Pull apart and eat.
Serves 10.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk.
Add pie filling.
Mix well; add remaining ingredients.
Place in freezer until hard.
Take out 30 minutes before serving.

title: pinto beans
directions: Rinse pinto beans; cover with water and add boiling meat or bacon grease, salt, onion, ketchup, soda, chili powder and brown sugar.
You can add 1/2 pound meat 1 hour before done.
Cook until tender.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix ingredients well in long baking dish.
Place chicken around in mixture.
Cover with foil; bake for 2 hours at 425°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour and melted margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with pecans.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread on first layer. Mix together pudding and milk.
Spread on second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Let set 4 to 6 hours before serving in refrigerator.

title: ham spread
directions: Finely shred ham in food processor.
Add mayonnaise and relish.
Mix well and chill.
Sandwiches may be topped with tomato and/or lettuce.
Will last about 10 days in refrigerator.

title: marshmallow crispy treat in micro
directions: Microwave margarine in large microwave-safe bowl on High for 45 seconds, or until melted.
Add marshmallows; toss to coat with margarine.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes, or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Immediately add cereal, mixing lightly until well coated.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool, then cut into about 24 squares.

title: lasagna
directions: In hot oil, saute the garlic and onion until soft.
Add ground meat. Cook until crumbly. Mix in seasonings.
Add tomato paste and water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Layer with noodles and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 generous servings.

title: *beet salad
directions: Add enough water to beet juice to make a cup; bring to a boil and dissolve jello.
Add lemonade and salt; chill slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold.
Let set until firm. Serves 8.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add hamburger; cook until colored, but do not brown.
Salt and pepper.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan 1/2 chopped cabbage, meat mixture and remaining cabbage.
Spoon the tomato soup over the top.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Five minutes before serving, top with slices of American cheese.

title: garlic french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar and shake well.
Makes 3/4 cup dressing.

title: "polish mistakes"
directions: Brown meats separately and drain.
Combine with cheese and seasonings.
Cool slightly.
Spread on rye breads.
These can be frozen on cookie sheets.
Once frozen, transfer to freezer bags and store in freezer.
When ready to use, bake on cookie sheets in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes until cheese is bubbly.

title: rice and shrimp dip
directions: Cook rice as directed on package (no butter).
Combine hot rice and all other ingredients in a bowl.
Serve chilled.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn and mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: another jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Soften cream cheese in microwave; add to Jell-O.
Whisk to break up and melt cream cheese completely.
Add cold water.
Put into refrigerator until almost set.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion (drain some liquid).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat oil in skillet.
Drop potato mixture by spoonful into skillet.
Fry until crisp and golden brown. Drain on brown paper.
Serve with applesauce.

title: honey oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, raisins, nuts, brown sugar and salt.
Add milk, oil, egg and honey.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill 12 greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: fantastic pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes.

title: aunt sophia's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan (10 x 10-inch).
Stir in, all at once, flour, baking powder, salt, 1/3 cup sugar and milk.
Put fruit over this mixture.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar.
Pour water or juice over all.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: sausage apple dressing
directions: Fry sausage lightly.
Add apples, onions, salt, pepper, hot water and crumbs.
Mix well.

title: alpha kappa meeting night casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles; toss with salt and pepper and 2 tablespoons butter.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top noodles with sauerkraut and shredded corned beef.
Spread dressing over beef and top with shredded Swiss cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no-bake peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Put in crust and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
This is even more tasty if you use crunchy peanut butter.

title: stuffed pork chops ol
directions: Combine cooked rice, cheese, pecans, green pepper, celery, and thyme.
Fill each pocket with 1/4 to 1/3 cup of stuffing. Lightly brown chops in lard or drippings.
Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper, place on rack in roasting pan and cover securely with foil.
Bake in a moderate oven (350 degrees) for 30 minutes. Uncover and continue baking for 30 minutes longer or until meat is done.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Serve on crackers or bread.

title: beef casserole
directions: Start your oven at 325° or slow.
Cut onion, celery and green pepper coarsely.
Chop leftover beef in small cubes.
Cook beef in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine for several minutes (if using ground beef, cook until brown) and transfer to a medium-size casserole.
Put remaining butter or margarine in pan; toss in chopped vegetables and cook until limp.
Stir in mushroom soup, water, salt, pepper and mix in with the beef.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
At the end of this time, remove cover; sprinkle surface with Chinese noodles and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: cracker snack
directions: Stir dressing mix, oil and seasonings together.
Pour over crackers.
Stir now and then until oil is absorbed.
Store in an airtight container.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water and add butter.
After butter has melted, add sugar.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to mixture.
Add buttermilk, then beaten eggs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in 2 (9-inch) layer pans.

title: hawaiian style rice salad
directions: Combine
all ingredients (except almonds).
Toss lightly. Serve
on beds of salad greens or lettuce.	Sprinkle with almonds.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Thoroughly cream butter with sugar and rind.
Add egg yolks; beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in lemon juice, flour, cereal and milk.
(Mixture will look curdled, but this will not affect finished product.)
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased one quart baking dish; place the dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched.
When done, pudding has a cake-like layer on top with custard below.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix and roll between wax paper.
Makes 2 single crust pies.

title: the cake that doesn't last
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well but do not beat.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins, sour cream, eggs and spices.
Bring to a boil and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and whipped cream.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture into pie shell.
Add cooled raisin mixture and other 1/2 of the cream cheese mixture.
Chill and garnish if desired with sweetened whipped cream.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Cut cabbage; sprinkle salt and water.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut celery and pepper; let stand 20 minutes (drain off).
Mix all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil and pour over cabbage.
Let cool, pack and freeze.

title: in advance breakfast
directions: Mix and let set overnight. Refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: classic lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water with olive oil and salt until tender; drain.
Brown ground beef with garlic, basil and oregano; drain off any grease and set aside.

title: cheese nibbles
directions: Soften butter or margarine to room temperature; mix with cheese.
Add flour, pecans and salt and pepper to taste.
Form into small patties and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: german cucumbers
directions: Line bowl with lettuce leaves covered with a layer of thinly sliced tomatoes.
Peel cucumbers and slice paper thin.
Add salt. Cover and refrigerate 4 hours.
Rinse, dress and press out excess liquid.
Mix with onion.
Mix other ingredients and add just before serving.
Arrange in the tomato-lettuce lined bowl.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Preheat broiler.
Halve each tomato crosswise.
Place, cut side up, in a shallow baking pan.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, butter and basil; sprinkle over tomatoes.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from the heat source for about 4 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook beef and onions in skillet.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and water.
Stir well.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Turn into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lay bread in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Brown sausage and drain.
Combine milk, eggs and dry mustard in bowl.
Layer sausage and cheese over bread.
Pour on egg mixture.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate orange cream
directions: You will need 5 chocolate dessert cups (optional).

title: peppermint crunch
directions: Melt chocolate and stir in peppermint chips.
Spread on waxed paper; let stand until firm.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes great holiday candy snacks.

title: brenda's stuffed chicken with crab
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter and flour; stir 1 minute.
Slowly add milk, broth and wine.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Set aside. Saute onions in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add crab, mushrooms, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir in 2 tablespoons of sauce.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Stir syrup, peanut butter and sugar in heavy saucepot over very low heat until bubbly (until sugar seems to be melted). Pour over corn flakes; stir well. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or buttered cookie sheet.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, syrup, butter, vanilla and pecans to beaten eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Place all vegetables plus chestnuts and mushrooms into a large bowl.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Pour over vegetables; mix.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: molten chocolate
directions: Lightly butter 6 custard cups. Combine the chocolates and butter in microwavable bowl and heat on Medium until the chocolate is melted, stirring occasionally. Remove and stir in sugar until smooth (sugar won't be dissolved). Add eggs, flour, baking powder and cocoa. Beat with mixer on medium-high speed until the mixture is pale and has a thick mousse-like consistency, about 5 minutes. Divide mixture among custard cups. Cover each with plastic wrap . Freeze at least 3 hours or several days.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender.
Place in casserole dish. Cover with brown sugar, salt and butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and return to oven. Cook until brown.

title: bishop bread
directions: Mix flour, salt, brown sugar, cinnamon and shortening.
Save 1/4 cup of mixture. Add baking powder, eggs, soda and buttermilk; pour in greased loaf pan. Sprinkle 1/4 cup crumbs. Pat smooth. Bake at 350° until done.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil.
After syrup starts boiling, boil for 5 minutes, without stirring.
Remove from stove and add baking soda and vanilla. Pour syrup over popcorn, mixing well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in a covered container.
Use 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons of the mix to one cup of hot water.
Yields 45 to 50 servings.

title: nuts-for-chocolate balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup sugar in small bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until coarse crumbs.
Press firmly into bottom of a greased, foil lined 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: one meal (skillet)
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in large iron skillet and cook over medium heat until vegetables are crisp-tender and all the pink is gone from the meat.
Add the potatoes and the tomatoes. Simmer, stirring frequently to prevent sticking, for about 15 minutes.
Put in a 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Add the salad and garlic bread and you have a fine meal for 4 people.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Pour Doritos in casserole.
In frying pan, cook hamburger. Add both soups, enchilada sauce and green chilies.
Pour over Doritos.
Top with cheese and onion and bake until cheese is melted.

title: seven-up jello
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix cream cheese in hot Jell-O. Add sugar, pineapple, nuts and 7-Up.
Pour into Pyrex cake pan. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Beat remaining ingredients together.
Layer broccoli, then mixture, alternating.
Cover all broccoli.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Can easily be frozen before or after cooking.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix together graham crackers and margarine.
Mix in 2 tablespoons powdered sugar.
Pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan; bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 8 ounce package cream cheese and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill for 3 hours.
(Can use blueberry pie filling.)

title: egg pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk and mix well.
Add flour; mix well. Add vanilla and margarine and mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for about 15 or 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: dieter's orange kiss-me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Combine butter, brown sugar, egg and Sweet*10.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, orange extract and orange juice.
Blend at low speed until moistened about 1 minute.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until light golden brown.

title: the best sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, oil and eggs with vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to already creamed ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill dough and roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with glass dipped in sugar. Dough may be rolled out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.

title: horseradish cheese ball
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.
Shape into a ball.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
May also be rolled in chopped parsley.

title: avocado fabulous first course(servings:  4)
directions: Allow 1/2 avocado and 1/3 can of consomme per serving.
Dice avocado and toss with lemon juice.
Place in bottom of balloon wine glass.
Cover with consomme, sprinkled with a little additional lemon juice.
Add a dollop of sour cream and sprinkle with capers.
Serve as appetizer or first course.
Can be made ahead 1 hour before company arrives and kept in refrigerator.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients at least 3 hours before you want to serve it.
Serve in dark brown bread (a loaf) that has been hollowed out.
Put pieces of bread around loaf and serve.

title: fried catfish
directions: Rinse fillets and soak in salt water for 5 minutes. Drain. In a paper sack, combine cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper. Mix well. Drop in fillets and shake to coat. Drop in fry pan with hot oil. Cook until fish floats, turning once to brown other side.

title: lemon gooey
directions: Mix together margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Press into bottom of a 8 1/2 x 11-inch or larger cake pan.
Beat well the cream cheese, 2 eggs and box of sugar.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over cake mixture.
Pour cream cheese mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until light brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add milk and extract. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Fold in coconut.
Bake in a well greased and floured tube pan. Put in a cold oven and turn to 325°. Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tests done.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in a little oleo. Mix hot rice with drained broccoli, Cheez Whiz, onion and bell peppers and soup. Bake in casserole for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: never fail texas crust
directions: In a small bowl combine water, egg and vinegar.
Mix well. In a large bowl combine flour (spoon into cup lightly), sugar, salt and Crisco.
Cut ingredients in large bowl together.
Mix well.
Add well mixed ingredients of small bowl to large bowl. Mix well until large ball forms.
Divide into 5 parts and refrigerate 1 hour.
Proceed as for any crust.

title: grandma terry's pineapple turnovers
directions: Dissolve yeast
in 1/4 cup water. Mix in flour and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cover and chill for one hour.
Roll dough on pastry sheet sprinkled with sugar.
Cut into squares, fill with Pineapple Filling, fold into triangles and crimp edges.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: breakfast baked omelet
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with bread.
Layer on cheese, ham, onion and mushrooms.
Beat milk, eggs, mustard and salt and pour over ingredients in pan.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: waffles
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 1 cup warm water with the sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix flour and 3 cups water in yeast mixture and let stand at room temperature overnight (about 6 to 8 hours). Batter will be lumpy.
Place about 1 1/2 cups batter in a jar and place in refrigerator for starter the next time you make hotcakes. DO NOT put the lid on tight, as it will explode; what a mess.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa 3 times.
Mix buttermilk, vinegar and food coloring together.
Add alternately with flour mixture.
Beat well.
Fold in soda.
Do not beat soda.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes, then ice.

title: vanilla shortbread
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°, then grease the baking pan.
Measure the butter into the mixing bowl.
Add powdered sugar to the butter.
Mix thoroughly and then add the vanilla.
Add the flour and knead the mixture with your hands until it forms one smooth lump.
Press the dough into a baking pan.
Smooth the top with a spatula.
Prick the dough lightly with a fork.
Put the baking pan in the oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut them into squares with a knife.
Put the squares aside to cool.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour in mixing bowl.
Add melted butter and stir well.
Add eggs and vanilla, stirring well to make sure eggs are distributed through batter.
Add pecans; stir to coat nuts.
Pour in pie shell and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding mix until it turns green. Drain oranges and add to pineapple and pudding mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 1/2 hour before serving.

title: krieger thanksgiving squash
directions: Saute onions in butter; add eggs.
Combine all ingredients, except crackers.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: beef stew pie
directions: Place pie crust in pie pan.
Pour beef stew into crust.
Top with cheese.
Place second pie crust on top and pinch edges around top of crust rim.
Bake at 350° until crust is done, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening until the size of small peas.
Blend egg, vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture a little at a time.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Place in pan; prick with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
This makes 3 (10-inch) pie crusts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake until melted.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine dressing, soy sauce and ginger.
Pour over chicken; marinate overnight or several hours in refrigerator.
Place wings on broiler pan.
Broil 15 to 20 minutes, turning once.
Brush occasionally with marinade.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar slowly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavoring, add sifted dry ingredients slowly; then add cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 300° to 325° or until done.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Add peanut butter, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Spoon onto waxed paper (using teaspoon for small candies) and cool.

title: german cabbage rolls
directions: Boil head of cabbage until you can work with leaves.
Cut thick veins off bottom of backs of leaves.
Brown bacon and remove from grease.
Set both aside.
Combine beef, pork, bread, eggs, onion and spices to taste.

title: potato candy
directions: Combine potato, butter, coconut and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Gradually add the powdered sugar.
Press into buttered pan, making it about an inch thick.
Melt bitter chocolate over boiling water.
Spread over potato mixture and put in a cold place for about 2 hours.
Cut in squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together well.
Shape into loaf and place in a 7 1/2 x 10-inch Pyrex dish sprayed with Pam.
Spread top with catsup thickly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate coca-cola cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, soda into bowl. Put in saucepan the Coke, cocoa and margarine; bring to a boil. Stir into flour mixture. Add buttermilk, eggs and marshmallows. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken for frying.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dip in sauce, put in well-greased paper bag, any sauce left pour in bag too.
Twist bag and fasten end.
Place in 350° oven and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Pick shells from crab meat.
Combine all ingredients and add to crab meat.
Form into cakes and fry until brown.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: Bake cake as per instructions on box.
Mix pudding with milk and Kahlua in bowl.
Break Heath bars into pieces.
Crumble cake and layer with pudding, Cool Whip and Heath bars in large glass bowl or punch bowl.

title: home made ice cream
directions: Mix together. Makes 6 quarts.

title: london broil marinade
directions: Blend marinade and water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Pierce steak with fork and let lay in marinade 15 to 30 minutes. Turn once.
Broil or barbecue.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake in large tube pan at 275° for two hours.
Cool on wire rack.
Turn onto serving plate.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Yields 16 servings.

title: great orange roughy
directions: Lay fish in dish; sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Spread picante sauce over each piece.
Melt butter or margarine and mix with juice from lemon.
Pour butter mixture over fish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: diabetic fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Boil until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O.
Pour over strawberries.
Cool slightly before putting into pie shell. Refrigerate.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Top each with a slice of cheese.
Dilute soup with water and pour over chicken and cheese.
Toss stuffing and butter together.
Sprinkle over top. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: already ready turkey casserole
directions: Combine process cheese spread and milk.
Mix well - until smooth.
Toss shell roni with margarine.
Combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Spoon into 2 quart casserole, cover.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot.
Stir before serving.

title: easy noodle bake
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms and garlic; saute until mushrooms are tender.
Remove from heat.
Add noodles and remaining ingredients except cheese, stirring gently.
Transfer mixture to a 1-quart casserole dish sprayed with vegetable spray.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Uncover; bake 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados, cut them in halves and remove pits. Toss with lemon juice in a ceramic bowl.
Mash with a fork until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Adjust seasoning to taste.

title: chocolate coconut chess pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Garnish with whipped cream or topping, if desired.
Yields 3 pies, 2 for lunch and 1 for a friend.

title: meat dip
directions: Fry hamburger until done and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Take each piece of bun and roll into a ball.
Roll into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Put balls into a Bundt pan (evenly).
Melt butter, 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Pour over the balls in pan. Bake 1/2 hour in 350° oven.
Turn over right away on a plate.
Pull apart balls and eat.

title: perfect sugar cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and then refrigerate dough for two hours. Roll out 1/3-thick and use cutter for your favorite design.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Eat plain or frost them.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix mashed bananas and eggs in a bowl.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into moist mixture until well blended, but do not beat. Add butter and nuts (melt butter). Pour batter into well-greased and floured loaf pans (9 x 5-inch).
Let stand for about 10 minutes before baking.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, sugar, cooking oil and milk.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Knead on floured board and put into large, greased bowl.
Cover and put in refrigerator.

title: southwestern chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound double breasts slightly.
Spread lightly with mustard. In center place piece of Monterey Jack cheese, piece of ham, piece of green chili.
Roll each breast and secure with toothpick.
In oiled pan, place breasts.
Sprinkle with paprika for color and drizzle with olive oil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: chicken salad
directions: Slice each pineapple chunk in half.
Toss together the first 6 ingredients.
Thoroughly combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put all ingredients together in a mixing bowl and stir well. Bake in lightly greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes in a 350 degree oven.
Cool 35 to 40 minutes before sprinkling powdered sugar over top, if desired.
We do not use powdered sugar.
We use Cool Whip in place of powdered sugar.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and celery in skillet.
Put in bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle uncooked rice on top.
Cover with mushroom and chicken soups.
Add 1 can of water if Minute rice is used, 2 cans if raw rice is used.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover first 45 minutes and uncovered last 15 minutes.

title: stir-n-roll biscuits
directions: Mix and sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Beat together liquid fat and milk.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients gradually.
Roll out between wax paper.
Fold over. Cut out.
Place in greased baker.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 475° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In 1 tablespoon butter, brown beef and add tomato sauce.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, scallions and green pepper.

title: eagle brand chocolate cake
directions: Heat together first five ingredients.
Add to flour mixture, then add eggs.
Mix well.
Bake in cookie sheet pan 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: frontier jerky
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients except meat.
Stir to mix well.
Place meat 3 or 4 layers deep in a glass stoneware, plastic or stainless steel container, spooning liquid smoke mixture over each layer.
Cover tightly.
Marinate 6 to 12 hours in the refrigerator, stirring occasionally and keeping the mixture tightly covered.
Place in oven at 200° until desired dryness or crispness, approximately 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 1/4 pound jerky.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken until done.
Debone into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in broth (add salt); dice onion and bell pepper and saute in butter until done.
In large casserole dish, scoop spaghetti from broth.
Add chicken, pimentos, tomatoes, onion and bell pepper.
Slice cheese and lay on top. Heat at 350° until cheese melts.

title: those things-dessert
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, butter and powdered sugar until crumbly. Pat in bottom of square or round pan (well-greased).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and orange rind.
Mix well.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup boiling water to dissolve sugar.
Refrigerate while preparing Jell-O.
Stir Jell-O into 1 cup boiling water until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water; chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in cranberry mixture, celery, apples and walnuts.
Pour into 2 (3 cup) molds or 1 (6 cup) mold. Cover and chill until set.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: christmas coffee
directions: Mix together and store in a tin.
Add to boiling water to taste.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in jackets until tender. Peel and mash to make 2 cups. Cream until smooth and combine with other ingredients. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and cook for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: peppermint schnapps
directions: Boil sugar and water together to thin syrup stage.
Cool.
Add vodka and peppermint extract.
Combine well to blend.
Store in bottles with tight fitting caps.

title: orange or lime jello salad
directions: Combine orange Jell-O, pineapple and juice.
Let it come to a boil.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts.
Let congeal. This makes 2 casseroles.
For smaller amount make 1/2 of recipe. This can be frozen.
Lime Jell-O can be used instead of orange.

title: mom's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x
13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Do not overbake.

title: sally lun bread
directions: Scald milk and add sugar, butter and salt.
Cool to lukewarm and add well beaten eggs, yeast and flour to make a stiff batter. Place dough in well greased bundt pan and cover with towel and let rise one hour.
Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese burger pie
directions: Mix ingredients together (except cheese slices and pie crust) and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add one layer of cheese slices over the hamburger mixture, then cover with the pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: special k cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips in large pan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Special K cereal, mixing well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Chill.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl in order given and refrigerate overnight.
Mix just before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a 2-quart greased casserole.
Mix the following and sprinkle over the top:
brown sugar, 1/3 cup melted margarine, flour, and chopped pecans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: black forest freezer pie
directions: Spoon ice cream into pie crust; cover and freeze for 15 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar until smooth; fold in whipped topping.
Spread over pie. Using the back of a spoon, make an 8 inch diameter well in the center of the pie for the pie filling.
Cover and freeze for 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
May be frozen for up to 2 months.
Just before serving, spoon pie filling into well; drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add the pudding mix. Let the frozen bread thaw.
Cut up into small balls.
Put 1/2 in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add mixture.
Cut up remaining bread; put in pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(May also use 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 can tomato soup, cabbage and water.
Cut out heart of the cabbage and immerse in boiling water to loosen leaves.
Place about 2 tablespoons of meat mixture into each leaf.
Roll and fasten with toothpicks.
Place in a large roasting pan.
Mix remaining can of soup with the 1 cup water and pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Makes about 40 cabbage rolls.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Roll in nuts.

title: mexically corn bread
directions: *Note:
If salsa is runny, use less.

title: potato logs
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Beat in cream cheese, 2 tablespoons oleo, onion, parsley and seasonings.
Using 1/2 cup for each log, shape in 12 (4-inch) logs.
Stir melted remaining butter or oleo into crumbs, cheese and paprika.
Coat logs.
Place in single layer in greased 7 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
May be made a day ahead. Bake until puffy.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla. Beat in eggs. Blend in chocolate. Stir in flour and nuts. Bake in a greased 8 x 8 x 2 pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and cut into 16 squares.

title: spinach - water chestnut dip
directions: Thaw and press all water out of spinach.
Mix all ingredients together, except bread.

title: fruit-nut cheese mold
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point; add gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Chill until partially set.
Soften cream cheese; stir in pimento.
Add to gelatin mixture and blend.
Fold in whipped cream, celery and nuts.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill firm.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown meat well.
Mix together other ingredients with meat. Bake in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°. Freezes well.

title: ground beef barbecue
directions: Chop onion into small pieces; melt shortening in large skillet and brown onion and ground beef.
(Drain off fat.) Mix sugar, mustard, vinegar and catsup in medium saucepan and warm over medium heat.
Add browned ground beef and onion to the sauce.
Mix well and simmer until hot.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Mix.
Add baking powder to flour; sift.
Alternately add flour and milk to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Roll on floured pastry cloth.
Cut. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost and decorate.

title: scrambled eggs for twelve
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Beat eggs, sour cream, salt and milk.
Stir in sauteed onions and bacon.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish
and bake at 325° until eggs are set and moist, about 30 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, vanilla and salt on low speed about 1 minute.
Gradually add flour at low speed until just combined.
Stir in nuts.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until firm to the touch but not brown (do not overbake).
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool, then re-roll in powdered sugar.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Last 15 minutes, crush potato chips and put on top.

title: italian bread
directions: Used for pizza crusts, dinner rolls, loaves of bread and bread sticks.
Mix everything together.
Knead 5 to 8 minutes.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and shape as desired.
Bake pizza at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes, rolls/breadsticks at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes or loaves (small) at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma's homemade cottage cheese
directions: Here is a recommended method that reduces the time from the usual 6 hours to about 1 hour (for rendering alone).
Most of the odor of rendering is eliminated.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown hamburger, not past pink.
Add mushrooms and onion; drain.
Add gravy to this.
Turn heat off skillet.
Beat egg and mix everything together.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with slashed crust.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Season to taste.

title: mini chocolate chip cakes
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Place vinegar in a 1 cup measure and fill with milk to the 1 cup line.
Set aside.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Soak chopped dates in boiling water and soda.
Mix sugar, oleo, beaten egg and vanilla.
Mix baking powder, flour, salt and nuts.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add date mixture and bake in 9 x 14-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease bottom only of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pecans and coconut together and spread in bottom of pan.
Prepare German chocolate cake mix according to package directions and pour over pecan and coconut mixture.
Blend the last 4 ingredients and spoon over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: never fail corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Grease casserole.
Put in mixture and pour 2 tablespoons melted butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: plain tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients including enough flour to make the consistency of biscuit dough.
Roll out and cut out.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring and then the vanilla wafers.
Mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Mix.
Cook in tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
Serve plain or with frosting.

title: hearty stir-fry
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to directions.
In medium skillet, cook sausage until no longer pink.
Drain,
reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add cabbage, onion, apple and garlic. Stir-fry just until tender.
Stir in salt and sage.
Add spaghetti.
Cook and stir until hot.
Remove from heat; add cheeses and toss to mix.
Arrange on warm platter.
Garnish as desired.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce and simmer until flavor is well blended.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan; layer on cheese and sour cream.
Top with crescent rolls so they meet; brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 375° until rolls are brown, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green beans with garlic
directions: Cook garlic and celery until just tender in hot butter in a large heavy skillet.
Add beans.
Cover and cook (break frozen blocks apart with fork as they thaw) about 5 minutes or until beans are just tender.
Sprinkle hot beans with seasoned salt.
Pour into a heated serving bowl and top generously with buttered browned sliced almonds.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Place first five ingredients in blender in layers and pack down.
Add the tomatoes and juice.
Pulsate blender until desired consistency.
Makes approximately 1 quart.
Delicious!!

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt into mixer bowl. Add oil, vinegar and vanilla to dry ingredients while mixing at low speed. Pour water over all ingredients in bowl. Mix at low speed until all ingredients are blended. Pour into greased pan and bake.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, peppers, onions and garlic salt.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on each shell and roll up.
Chill.
Slice into bite-size pieces and serve with picante sauce.
Recipe is easily doubled to feed a larger crowd.

title: mississippi caviar
directions: Drain peas and layer with onions.
Sprinkle each layer with pepper (be generous).
Combine oil, vinegar, garlic and salt in blender at high speed for 3 minutes or until thoroughly mixed. Pour over peas and onions.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Will keep 2 weeks and gets better all along.
Serves 8.

title: gavatini
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Place in casserole; add spaghetti sauce.
Add Mozzarella cheese (save some for top).
Mix well.
Add remaining cheese to the top.
Bake at 350° just until heated through and cheese is melted, approximately 30 minutes.

title: hot tuna salad(luncheon dish)
directions: Mix soup, tuna, celery, onion, mayonnaise and pepper.
Fold in egg slices.
Pile lightly into individual baking shells or a 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with crushed potato chips.
Bake in very hot 450° oven for 15 minutes or until hot.
Top with additional egg slices and parsley.
Makes 12 to 14 servings. Serve hot baking powder biscuits or hot rolls and assorted relishes.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Boil the potatoes with skins on.
When the potatoes are done, peel and put through a ricer.
Spread riced potatoes on a dish towel to remove moisture.
Put in a large bowl and sprinkle with salt. Add eggs, flour, bread crumbs and nutmeg.
Work together until mixture forms into dry balls.
If too wet, add more bread crumbs.
Roll into balls. Drop into salted boiling water. When balls rise to the surface of the water, reduce heat and simmer gently 3 to 5 minutes.
Take out one and cut it through the middle. The center should be dry, not soggy.
Remove balls from the water with a slotted or wire spoon.
Place on a hot platter. Don't boil too long or the balls will fall apart.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Drain water out of cans of veggies. Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
This recipe can be substituted with any raw veggies.
Boiled shrimp goes well also.

title: esther overbeay's rhubarb cake
directions: Mix rhubarb and 1/2 cup sugar; let stand until batter is mixed.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
When cake is mixed, add rhubarb to the mixture and bake at 350° (325° for glass) for 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Remove from pan; add onion.
Cook until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and bacon pieces.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage soup or string bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes and cook about 1/2 hour.
Add potatoes and cook together until done.
Brown 1/2 cup flour in 1/3 cup oil.
When well browned, add minced onion; stir well for 2 minutes and then pour into saucepan of soup and let come to a boil.
Ready to serve.
(String Bean Soup with same ingredients.)

title: recipe for preserving children
directions: Mix the children with dogs and empty into the field, stirring continuously.
Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Pour the brook gently over the pebbles.
Cover all of this with a deep blue sky and bake in the hot sun.
When children are well browned, they may be removed.
They will now be ready to set away to cool in the bathtub.
When any of the ingredients are missing (except the children), substitute any of the following four recipes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in a small pan; add water gradually and stir constantly.
Bring to a boil and cook for five minutes, stirring to keep from scorching.
Remove from fire and add remaining ingredients.
Serve warm or cold.

title: walnut squares
directions: Combine and bake at 325°
for 1/2 hour.
Cut in squares while hot.
Leave in pan to cool.

title: breakfast cake
directions: Add yogurt, oil, eggs and peel; beat well.
Add sugar, flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in fruit.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: peach salad
directions: Chop the peach pie slices.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: walnut waffles
directions: In a large bowl, combine pancake mix, walnuts, whey protein and cinnamon.
Blend milk, egg whites and applesauce in a blender. Add the wet mix to the dry, mixing thoroughly.
Set waffle iron to low for soft waffles or medium to high for the crisper variety. Coat waffle griddle with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour a quarter of the mixture into the waffle iron.
The waffle iron will automatically tell you when it's done.
Makes 4 large waffles.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: french market soup mix
directions: Sort and wash 2 cups bean mix; place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans and soak overnight.
Drain beans and add 2 quarts water and add next 3 ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove ham hock from soup and remove meat. Chop meat and return to soup.
Yield:
Approximately 2 1/2 quarts, 10 to 12 servings.

title: cahact
directions: Combine ground beef, sausage, eggs, bell pepper, onion, bread crumbs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in bottom of deep round casserole to approximately 1 1/2 inches deep.
Cut cabbage in wedges.
Place in boiling water for 1 to 2 minutes, until wilted and bright in color.
Place layer of cabbage on raw meat loaf. Place mashed potatoes on top of cabbage.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours, until a brown crust has formed on top of potatoes and meat mixture is done.
Serve while piping hot.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Saute onions in butter in large skillet until translucent. Stir in chicken, salsa and seasoning mix.
Simmer, uncovered, over low heat for 15 minutes or until chicken is cooked.

title: heavenly broiled fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Place fillets in a single layer on a well-greased bake and serve platter, 15 x 10-inches.
Brush fillets with lemon juice and let stand for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Broil fillets about 4 inches from source of heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove from heat and spread with cheese mixture. Broil 2 to 3 minutes longer or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Butter sides of 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and milk.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball in cold water.
Cool before beating.
Let butter melt on top of hot mixture.
Do not jar candy while cooling.

title: smoked sausage with gravy
directions: Fry sausage in butter until brown.
Remove sausage from pan and keep warm.
Add onion and mushrooms to pan and cook until onions are soft.
Remove from pan and put with sausage.
Add beef broth to pan and thicken with cornstarch paste.
Add sausage, mushrooms and onions and heat through.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Set aside. Mix sugar, oil and vinegar. Heat until sugar dissolves. Cool. Pour over the mixed vegetables. Let set overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake biscuit quarters in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Distribute coated biscuit pieces evenly around a buttered Bundt pan.
Melt butter in a saucepan; add remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture to margarine.
Stir until sugar is dissolved some and pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove bread to a cake plate immediately.
When cooled, make glaze of 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add just enough evaporated milk to pouring consistency.

title: chili
directions: Heat the oil in a heavy pan over medium heat and add beef, onion and garlic.
Cook until lightly browned.
Add the remaining ingredients, except for the salt, and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 1 hour.
Skim occasionally and season with salt.

title: cherry crumble
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Take off heat.
Stir in cake mix and lemon juice.
Pour cherries in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Crumble cake mixture over cherries. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until the top browns.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomatoes and blend until smooth.
Add tomato chunks and mix well.
Can be used as a dip or topping for tacos and tostados.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: eggplant mozzarella
directions: Beat eggs and milk together with fork until smooth.
Heat 1/4 inch oil in frying pan over low heat.
Dip eggplant into egg and milk mixture and roll in bread crumbs.
Dip eggplant again into egg and milk and re-roll in bread crumbs.
Let dry on wire racks several minutes, then fry in tho oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: sherbet punch
