directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: apple dip
directions: Whip cream cheese and brown sugar.
Add peanuts and vanilla. Cut apples in wedges and dip in sauce.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all together and drop on greased, medium hot griddle. Cook until brown on each side.

title: butter rum frosting
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Beat in confectioners sugar; add in rum and milk.
Beat until smooth and spreadable.

title: praline biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 2 teaspoons butter, 2 teaspoons brown sugar and 3 pecan halves in each 12 muffin cups.
Sprinkle cinnamon in each cup.
Heat in oven until melted.
Mix baking mix, applesauce and milk until dough forms.
Add some white sugar, beat 20 strokes.
Spoon mixture in cups.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: apricot cream dip
directions: Whisk ingredients in a small bowl.
Makes about 3/4 cup of dip.

title: south of the border shepherd's pie
directions: Prepare taco meat according to instructions.
In baking dish (9 x 13-inch), layer taco meat, corn and any other vegetables you may choose (black olives, tomatoes) and cornbread mix.
Bake until cornbread is golden brown.
Easy as pie!

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Season chicken with salt and pepper; rub with garlic and thyme.
Brown in hot oil in skillet. Remove from skillet.
Combine 2 tablespoons juice with cornstarch. Add honey, mustard and remaining juice to skillet.
Blend, then add browned chicken and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Stir cornstarch mixture into pan juices.
Add pineapple.
Cook, stirring until sauce thickens.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cheese soup(much better than campbell's!)
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until transparent in frying pan.
Add can of tomatoes and then fill empty can halfway with water and add that.
Blend together.
Add remaining ingredients, except pasta. Stir and simmer to a slow boil for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Cook pasta to taste.

title: cajun french fries
directions: Mix egg whites and cajun spices.
Dry French fries.
Drop in batter.
Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray.
Place fries on cookie sheet, trying not to let them touch each other.
Bake on the lower rack of a preheated 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Best french fries you ever had!
Money back guarantee!

title: caramel pineapple cake
directions: Put butter and brown sugar in an iron skillet.
Let it simmer for a few minutes.
Then add pineapple.
Then make a batter of eggs, sugar, water, vanilla, salt, baking powder, and flour.
Pour this over other mixture in skillet.
Bake in iron skillet in a hot oven for 10 minutes at 375° then reduce to 350° for 50 minutes. When done turn out of pan onto a large plate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: gina buckner's corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove cover; stir, then bake uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Cool, add marshmallows and nuts to chocolate mix.
Shape into 2 rolls, 1 to 2 inches in diameter.
Roll in coconut.
Chill and slice.
Serve.

title: saucy potatoes
directions: Combine soup and broth, stir in potatoes.
Cook over medium-low heat until it begins to simmer, and potatoes are heated through.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil water; add broccoli and onion.
Boil 10 to 12 minutes and drain.
Puree 1/2 of mixture.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add milk, cream and butter.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Mix flour and water separately, then blend into boiling mixture.
Stir rapidly.
Cook and stir until soup is consistency of heavy cream.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Combine all, mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: easy mix cookie bars
directions: Measure all ingredients into mixing bowl in the order listed. Do not stir until all are in the bowl.
Beat thoroughly.
Spread out on greased cookie pan, 17 x 11 x 2-inch.
Bake for 20 minutes or until rich brown.
When cool, frost with a thin layer of confectioners sugar frosting.
(I sometimes use a large cake pan for thicker bars.)

title: spice crackers
directions: Mix dry ingredients and crackers in plastic bag.
Add 1 cup oil.
Keep in refrigerator and shake once a day.
Great snack.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Wash pickles and slice.
Put in jars with 2 garlic buds and 2 heads of dill.
Heat vinegar mixture and pour over pickles.
Cold pack for 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Enough liquid for 6 pints.

title: cinnamon-and-spice trail mix
directions: Heat butter and honey in large skillet over medium heat until butter is melted.
Stir in cereal, tossing to coat well.
Cook, stirring often, for about 5 minutes or until cereal is toasted. Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in large bowl.
Add cereal and toss to coat well.
Stir in dried fruits.
Cool, then store in airtight container.
Makes 5 cups.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook vinegar, sugar, pepper, oil and water.
Bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute.
Mix vinegar mixture and vegetables.
Let set for half day and serve.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat rolls into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool. Mix next four ingredients and spread over crust.
Choose any or all of the vegetables to spread over creamed mixture, ending with cheese and black olives.
Cut and serve as a snack or appetizer.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream the butter and brown sugar. Stir in the egg, sour milk and molasses. Sift the dry ingredients and beat in a small amount at a time. Spoon heaped tablespoons of dough onto a greased cookie sheet and flatten with the bottom of a glass covered with a dampened cloth, dipped in granulated sugar. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: toffee cheesecake
directions: Beat the butter at medium speed in a mixing bowl until light. Add the brown sugar gradually, beating until fluffy. Add the flour and mix well. Stir in the pecans. Set aside 1 cup of the mixture. Press the remaining mixture over the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 14 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Pour liquid smoke over the beef in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with the celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt.
Refrigerate overnight in a covered baking dish.
Sprinkle both sides with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and bake at 200° to 225° for 4 to 5 hours, or until tender.
Uncover and pour the barbecue sauce over the meat.
Bake for 1 hour longer.
Serve hot in thick slices.

title: curried carrot soup(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Roast garlic cloves on pie plate in 325° oven for 30 minutes. Cool, peel and set aside.
Saute carrots, celery, onion and potato in butter over medium heat about 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to low. Sprinkle vegetables with flour and brown sugar, tossing to coat. Stir in milk until blended.
Add garlic, rosemary, curry, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, for 15 minutes.
Do not boil.
Puree in blender in several batches adding some broth to each batch.
Return puree to pot.
Stir in half and half and turmeric.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring often, about 15 minutes.
Stir wine into soup and add garnish.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Cook shrimp until they turn pink.
Mix onion, salt, buttermilk and garlic in blender.
Add mayonnaise.
Stir in shrimp and cheese.
Mix well and chill.

title: easter elegant-filled pork tenderloin
directions: Prepare wild rice according to directions on package.
With a sharp knife cut tenderloin lengthwise; do not cut all the way through.
Set aside.
In a skillet saute onions, apricots and mushrooms in butter; cook , stirring 3 to 5 minutes.
Add parsley and golden apricot nectar.
Cook gently 2 minutes longer.
Add to hot wild rice; mix thoroughly.
Spread center of tenderloin with wild rice mixture.
Tie meat securely with string.
Brush surface with oil or butter.
Set on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove string.
Slice and serve.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Add all water to Jell-O (as directed on box, except 1/2 cup). Add strawberries, thawed.
Cut up cake in small pieces.
Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: salmon with sizzling herbs
directions: Bring some water to a boil in the bottom of a steamer. Season the fish steaks on both sides with salt and pepper. Place the fish steaks in the top part of the steamer. Cover the pan and steam until the fish is opaque throughout, 7 to 8 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Beating at high speed, gradually sprinkle in sugar, a few tablespoons at a time.
Beat until sugar is completely dissolved. (Whites should stand in stiff peaks.)
Do not scrape sides of bowl during beating.
Beat in vinegar and vanilla.
Fold in pecan halves.

title: codfish salad
directions: Salt cod is not uniform in its saltiness; a small fillet that can be easily bent does not need as much soaking as a large piece that is stiff with salt.
Before cooking, all salt cod must be soaked in several changes of water.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine soup mix with bread crumbs.
Dip chicken into soup mixture, coating well.
Place in lightly greased baking pan and drizzle with butter.
Bake, turning once, for 10 minutes or until tender.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Place broccoli, which has been cooked according to directions on package, in bottom of greased casserole.
Add remaining ingredients which have been mixed together. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 persons.
I always double recipe when entertaining.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the beef. Add onions and celery and simmer to soften veggies. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until flavors blend. Serve on buns.

title: enchiladas(makes 18)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan for tortillas.
Cook hamburger meat in a saucepan.
Fry tortillas in hot grease 1/2 minute.
Place hamburger meat, onion and cheese on tortilla and roll.
Pour taco sauce, heated chili and hot sauce over tortillas. Cook until cheese is melted.

title: winner's circle pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and then butter.
Add walnuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Test with a toothpick.
Bake longer if necessary.
It should be chewy, not runny.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Let sit in fridge for 1 hour so spices mix in well.
Serve on your favorite crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour, salt and pepper to chicken stock and cook until it thickens.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish.
Top with pastry or pie shell.
You may put it on the bottom of casserole, also, if you wish.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: ole-timey cake
directions: For when you don't have the convenience of a boxed cake mix.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl beat sugar, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg; blend well.
Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
Stir in rolled oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chips ahoy delight
directions: Crumble all of the cookies except 5 in the bottom of a large rectangle dish.
Mix the Jell-O according to the package instructions.
Pour the Jell-O on top of the cookies.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crumble the 5 remaining cookies on top of the Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator.
This is better if it is made the night before serving.

title: black bean parmesan lasagna
directions: In a saucepan, cook the tomatoes and green onions, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Mash the tomatoes and add black beans and picante sauce.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin with garlic mustard
directions: Cut tenderloin into about 8 pieces diagonally and pound. Sprinkle meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Heat oil and butter in frying pan.
Add pork and cook about 3 minutes on each side. Remove pork to dish and keep warm.
Add garlic and onion to pan and saute one minute.
Stir in mustard and 1 tablespoon parsley. Pour over meat and garnish with remaining parsley.

title: anastasis galley goulash
directions: *Garlic, cumin, salt, pepper, caraway seed and paprika.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift 3 1/2 cups flour with soda and salt. Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.

title: copper kettle fudge
directions: Over low heat, stir sugar, evaporated milk, salt and butter until dissolved, then cook for 10 minutes.
Add chocolate chips, German sweet chocolate bars, Hershey chocolate bar, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nut meats.
Pour mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares after 30 minutes, then refrigerate to store.

title: peanut butter soup
directions: (I don't like peanut butter, but I do like this!)

title: lion's club barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Ready to go on your ribs or chicken.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and stir again.
With wire whisk, stir in sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Stir until batter is smooth.
Mix in pecans

title: deloris arnette's sand tarts
directions: Heat oven to 400° (moderately hot). Cream together sugar, butter and vanilla.
Mix in flour and pecans.
Shape dough into small balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet until set but not brown (10 to 12 minutes). While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: swedish apple cake
directions: For sauce, combine brown sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt in small baking dish.
Gradually stir in 1 cup water.
Add butter; set aside.

title: tom and jerry mix
directions: Beat egg whites with a pinch of salt until they leave the sides of bowl.
Whip egg yolks 10 minutes or until light yellow. Add spices and salt.
Add powdered sugar gradually to the yolks, then fold in egg whites.
This recipe keeps well or can be frozen. Mix with one jigger of dark rum, one jigger of brandy.
Add Tom and Jerry Mix; fill cup with boiling water and top with sprinkle of nutmeg.

title: crab salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, cilantro, onion, jalapenos and crabmeat.
Chop into small portions for dipping.
Combine all chopped ingredients together in a bowl.
Squeeze in lemon juice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Enjoy with tortilla chips.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Beat egg whites, adding sugar, one tablespoon at a time after egg whites are at stiff peaks.
Add vanilla; fold in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Place in oven.
TURN OVEN OFF!
Leave cookie sheet in oven overnight.
(Do not grease foil on cookie sheet.)

title: szechuan green beans(microwave recipe)
directions: Place garlic, ginger and onions in the work bowl of a food processor; process until finely chopped.
Remove to a large, fairly shallow, baking dish.
Add oil and pepper flakes. Microwave, uncovered, at 100% power for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, at 100% for 15 minutes, stirring 4 to 5 times.
Remove from oven; stir and serve hot or cold.

title: crown roast of pork
directions: Rub roast with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Place rib
ends
down
in
roasting pan.	Roast at 325° for 2 hours. Prepare
rice
or
cornbread dressing.
When roast has cooked
2 hours,
turn ends up and fill cavity with dressing. Place remaining
dressing in 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered	during last
30 minutes of roasting time.
Roast pork 1 hour
longer
or until
thermometer reaches 170°.
Make gravy with juices.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and lime juice in medium-size bowl. Blend in egg yolks; turn into cooled crust.
Heat oven to 325°. Beat egg whites with cream of tartar in small bowl until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until egg whites form stiff, glossy peaks.
Spoon over filling.
Spread to edge of crust to seal.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden.
Cool on wire rack to room temperature.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer until well blended.

title: fettuccine with gulf shrimp
directions: Cook the pasta until just done.
Drain and toss with a tablespoon or two of peanut oil.
Melt the butter in a large skillet and add the onions.
Saute for a minute over moderate heat and add the shrimp, tomato, basil, parsley and vermouth.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the pasta. Toss until hot and correct seasoning.
Serves 4.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake covered tightly for 3 hours at 325°.

title: egg and sausage puff
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 2-quart to 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: chicken noodles
directions: Cook noodles until done; drain well.
Add all soup and chicken; mix well.
Add small amount of butter (use your own taste).
Add small amounts of milk until smooth and creamy.
Heat and serve.

title: spaghetti meatball sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and
chopped
onions.
Dice green pepper. Add all ingredients together.
Cook
for
4 hours in hot water bath. I add some butter,
10 ounces catsup and a little clear jell, too.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat butter (or vegetable oil) and sugar together.
Add eggs and
banana.
Beat well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add	to
the
first	mixture
with milk and vanilla extract.
Beat
well and stir in the nuts, maraschino cherries and mini chocolate
chips.
Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, lined with wax paper at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roasted garlic potatoes
directions: Lightly grease a large cookie sheet.
Wash potatoes and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Mix oil, garlic and rosemary.
Brush on potatoes. Sprinkle with cheese and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, until lightly browned and crisp.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into prepared graham cracker crusts and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Beat all ingredients, except crabmeat, in mixer for 5 minutes. Fold in crabmeat.
This is best made a day ahead.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cranberry-raspberry jello
directions: Add 1 cup hot water to jello and 1/2 cup cold water; chill until partially thickened.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Fold in pineapple, orange, cranberries and walnuts.
Chill until firm.

title: egg roll
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Cook 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add taco mix and sauce to beef.
Let cool.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Add Western dressing.
Mix well and serve cold.
Makes a very large amount. Recipe can be cut in half.

title: tortellini primavera
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms, onion and garlic in margarine in a large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortellini. Mix well. Cook until mixture just begins to boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tortellini and cook until thoroughly heated.

title: soft and chewy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
In large bowl, blend sugars using an electric mixer set at medium speed.
Add butter and mix to a firm, grainy paste, scraping the sides of the bowl.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add flour and mix at low speed until just mixed.
Do not overmix.

title: ma flossie guffey's pound cake
directions: Have butter soft.
Cream the butter and sugar about 10 minutes.
Beat eggs together; add to butter and sugar.
Blend in flour and flavoring.
Beat all ingredients until mixed well.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix in order given.
May use one small package of lemonade mix, if desired (use 2 teaspoons per cup).

title: flipflop bars
directions: Line 8 x 8-inch pan with foil.
Butter.
In medium pan, combine peanut butter, syrup and sugar.
Cook until peanut butter is melted.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
Press evenly into baking pan.
In same saucepan, combine chocolate chips, syrup, sugar and butter.
Melt and stir in cereal.
Spread over first layer.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 bars.

title: saralee's pound cake
directions: Blend butter, margarine and shortening together until smooth. Add eggs one at a time and continue to blend.
Add sugar.
In a separate bowl, mix flour and baking powder together.
In measuring cup, mix milk, vanilla and lemon extract.
Alternate adding flour mixture and milk mixture with butter mixture, ending with flour mixture.
Keep smooth.
Place in floured and greased tube pan and place in cold oven.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes before inverting pan.

title: pineapple jello mold
directions: Mix water with Jell-O.
Add ice cream and mix until melted. Add pineapple and juice.
Pour in greased mold or bowl and refrigerate.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Place ribs in large dish.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour over ribs.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake at 400° until done, about 2 hours.

title: baked french toast
directions: Slice bread into 1-2 inch thick slices.
Place in greased 9X13 pan.
Mix cream, eggs and honey (or syrup) and pour over bread.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Dot with butter while still hot.
I have substituted skim milk and 1/2 egg whites with no problem, although not as rich.

title: dirt cake or pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread.
Take 1/2 package Oreo cookies or for large pan, a whole package.
Open and scrape all frosting.
Crumble in plastic bag finely and cover pudding.
Randomly place gummy worms around and in pan and over edge.

title: sugar-free banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers and oleo in pan.
Press evenly over bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk. Add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Spread over banana slices.
Spoon pineapple over pudding mixture; spread whipped topping over pineapple.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until ready to serve.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix vegetables, pepperoni and cheese.
Pour dressing over all and refrigerate overnight.

title: jiffy cake
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs, milk, salt, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat with mixer until light and smooth.
Pour into deep cake pan.
Mix chocolate with nuts and spread evenly over cake.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: In pan, fry sausage, onion, pepper and seasoning until pepper is tender.
Strain off grease.
Roll dough in rectangle; prick with fork to make air holes.
Fill with sausage, onion and pepper combo.
Sprinkle with cheese (roll like a jelly roll).
Beat egg; brush bread with egg.
Bake on cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy taco soup
directions: Cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink, drain.
Add beans, tomatoes, chili, cheese and seasonings. Reduce heat to low, cook and stir until cheese is melted.
Stir in 1 c. sour cream.
Heat through.
Do not boil.
Garnish with sour cream and taco chips.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and pour into greased baking dish.
Cover with English grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: make-ahead scrambled eggs
directions: Saute bacon; add chipped beef, butter and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Sprinkle flour and pepper into the pan.
Gradually stir in the milk and cook, stirring, until thickened.

title: old fashioned german poppy seed cake
directions: Scald milk and pour over poppy seed.
Let stand 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Cream mayonnaise and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder together. Add flour mixture and poppy seed mixture, alternately to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water, then add frozen strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Pour into large pan (13 x 9 x 1-inch) until firm.

title: butter fried apple rings
directions: Beat Bisquick, egg and milk until smooth.
Cut apples 1/8-inch thick.
Dip slices in batter.
Cook on hot griddle until golden brown.
Serve with syrup, jelly or powdered sugar.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Rub
the
lard into flour as for pie dough.
In another dish mix
molasses,
sugar
and
vanilla.
Dissolve
soda
in boiling water
and
mix
with
flour
and lard.
If not stiff enough, add more flour.
Cut
in
strips 3 x 2-inches wide and 1/4-inch thick. Prick with fork and bake at 375° in a greased and floured cookie sheet.
(Grease
and flour the cookie sheet and roll the dough on it.
Cut,
stick
and
bake, then recut when taken out of oven.)

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers to crumb.
Mix all ingredients.
Originally, a cigar box (odorless) lined with 2 to 3 layers of wax paper was used, but as we all know they are not that easy to find.
So, either fine a similar size box or use a loaf pan.
You are going to think I left out some type of liquid because of it being so difficult to mix, but I didn't.
Store air-tight in the icebox.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream Sugar and butter; add eggs one at a time. Add flour and cream alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Add vanilla. Cold oven. 300 degrees for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.

title: holiday lemonade
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add crackers.
Toss well with oil.
Ready to serve immediately.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip well.
Add all other ingredients and refrigerate.
You can use any flavor of jello.

title: strawberry freezer jelly
directions: Mix fruit and sugar thoroughly.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Mix water and Sure-Jell in a saucepan.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in fruit, stirring for 3 minutes.
Spoon quickly into 6 (1-cup) freezer containers. Tightly lids.
Let stand overnight.
Store in freezer next day.

title: hermits
directions: Beat sugar and oleo until fluffy; add one egg and beat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: ooey gooey butter cake
directions: Mix egg, cake mix and butter until crumbly.
Add chopped pecans.

title: salmon log
directions: Allow cheese to soften at room temperature.
Remove bones and skin from salmon.
Mash cheese with fork; add other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate in a covered bowl overnight.
Roll into a log and roll in chopped pecans before serving.
Serve with Triscuits or favorite cracker.

title: no bake peanut butter logs
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Add peanut butter and cereal mixing with hands, if needed.
Shape into 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch logs.
Chill. Spread top with chocolate frosting.
Yields 7 1/2 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread(yields 2 loaves)
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs well.
Add sugar, pumpkin and oil; beat.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture. Add nuts and raisins.
Blend well.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and raisins. Add to eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Bake on greased and floured cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 2 eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring. Add to butter mixture.

title: peanut brittle(microwave candy)
directions: Microwave sugar, peanuts, and salt 4 minutes on high.
Stir and microwave 3 more minutes on high.
Stir and add butter.
Cook 2 minutes longer on high.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Beat well. Quickly pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Break in pieces when cool.

title: beets in sour sauce
directions: Melt butter or oleo in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except beets.
Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add beets.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crab dip
directions: Saute chopped onion until golden.
Add garlic; saute 1/2 minute.
Add (picked) crab.
Cook until crab is heated through. Add cream cheese that has been whipped in electric mixer for 3 minutes.
(Do not use pre-whipped cream cheese.)
Saute, adding spices to taste.
Refrigerate overnight.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cheddar bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: "dog food"
directions: Melt together margarine, peanut butter and milk chocolate chips over low heat.
Pour on top of Crispix cereal and mix well. Pour 1 cup powdered sugar on bottom of large, brown paper bag. Dump in cereal mixture.
Pour 1 cup powdered sugar on top.
Close bag, then shake well.

title: pat-a-pie crust
directions: Into oil add milk and stir.
Pour in flour mixture.
Mix with fork until well-blended.
Roll up all into a ball.
Place in pie pan and press to shape crust.
Sides should be high.
Bake 10 - 15 minutes before filling.
If you double the recipe for a fruit-filled double crust, increase the baking time to 15 - 20 minutes.

title: tutti-frutti-chicken salad
directions: Toss together and chill.

title: surprise punch
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions.
Make syrup out of 1 cup sugar and 3 cups water.
Boil until clear.
Add Jell-O mixture to syrup.
Add 1 quart of pineapple juice, 1/2 cup fresh lemon and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract (actually, I like a little more...it smells soooo good!).
Mix all together.
Pour into plastic bags and tie.
Put into clean milk carton and freeze for 24 hours.

title: candy cane oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add sugar gradually. Beat until fluffy.
Add water.

title: sunrise punch
directions: Combine ingredients in a pitcher; stir well and chill.

title: peas with lettuce
directions: In a wide frying pan over light heat with butter, add lettuce and cook, stirring until 2 to 3 minutes.
Immediately stir in peas, parsley, sugar and nutmeg.
Cook until peas are heated and juices are boiling.
Season with salt.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: red potato wedges
directions: Place potatoes in a large bowl. Sprinkle with oil, rosemary, garlic powder and pepper; toss to coat. Place potatoes on a baking sheet that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray. Cover and bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Turn potatoes; bake, uncovered, 20 minutes longer or until browned. Yield: 4 servings.

title: oatmeal-apple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly. Sift flour with baking powder, soda, spices and salt.
Add milk, vanilla and flour mixture to the creamed mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Add oatmeal and chopped apples and stir well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet by the teaspoonful. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Combine ingredients and put in 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter. Steam broccoli until partially cooked, about 3 minutes.
Cool and press down.

title: aunt rose's chocolate pudding frosting
directions: Cook sugar, milk and chocolate on stove.
In cup, place 1/4 cup milk and add cornstarch; stir until smooth.
Add milk/cornstarch mixture to sugar mixture until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.

title: popcorn dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly and stuff in 12 to 14 pound turkey.
Close cavity with skewers.
Place in oven on rack in open pan.
Roast in moderate oven (325°) for 5 hours or desired stage of doneness.

title: layered cranberry salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; cook, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in lemon juice. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce; blend well.
Stir in celery and pecans.
Chill until partially set.
Add nutmeg to Cool Whip.
Fold in lemon mixture.
Spoon half of mixture into lightly oiled 7-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Spoon raspberry gelatin mixture over lemon mixture.
Chill until set. Spoon remaining lemon mixture over raspberry layer.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce.
Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Thaw lemonade and Cool Whip.
Mix with condensed milk until smooth.
Pour into pie crust.
Put into freezer or refrigerator until firm.
Serve cold.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well. Shape into small balls with floured fingers.
Place on baking sheets.
Press lightly with fork to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on wire racks.
Store in airtight container.

title: grandma's salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and use the juice plus water to make 1 cup. Bring this liquid to a boil and stir in the jello. Let the mixture cool and mix in the cream cheese. Add the rest of the ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: ponderosa relish
directions: Chop the first 5 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients in a pot large enough to allow slow boiling and cook for approximately 2 hours. Stir often to prevent scorching. Cook until relish reaches sauce-like thickness. Pour into sterilized jars and seal immediately. Makes approximately 4 pints.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add oregano and crushed pepper.
Spread mix in bottom of the pan.
Spread sauce, sprinkle onion, pepperoni and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove and add Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil and add onion, ginger root and chicken until it is browned.
Add the rest of the ingredients; hold out the garlic cloves.
Bring to a boil, then cover and put on low fire for one hour.
Turn chicken a few times while cooking.
Add sliced garlic 5 minutes before it's done.
Good served with rice.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, marshmallow cream and juice only from cherries. Mix very well.
Good, served over fruits or as a fruit dip.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Combine eggs and milk; stir in crumbs, onions, salt, sage and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Stuff bell peppers. Put in a deep baking dish.
Add 1/8 cup water to bottom of dish. Seal with foil; bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mom's chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper. Coat chicken with flour mixture. Pan fry until golden brown. Add onion to pan and saute until soft. Place in roaster pan. Add potatoes to chicken, cover with enough water to cover potatoes. Simmer on stove top at medium heat. When potatoes are softened, spoon dumplings on top of chicken and potatoes. Cook until set, about 10 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit cocktail cake ii
directions: Mix well the above ingredients.
Pour into greased pan. Sprinkle top of dough
with 1/2 cup coconut and 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Bake in slow oven, 300 degrees.
Makes 3 - 9 inch layers or 1 large loaf.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer about 20 minutes.
Pour into hot jars. Seal and process 30 minutes in water bath.
Makes about 6 half pints.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Combine flour and 1/4 teaspoon tarragon on a plate.
Put the egg substitute and bread crumbs on separate plates.
Dredge chicken in flour, then egg substitute and the bread crumbs.
In nonstick skillet, heat 1 teaspoon olive oil over medium heat.
Cook half the chicken for 5 minutes; turn.
Add second teaspoon of olive oil and continue the same with second batch of chicken until done.
Dust with pepper.
Remove from skillet.
Combine the chicken broth, Marsala and remaining 1/4 teaspoon tarragon.
Place minced garlic and shallot in hot pan with about 1/4 of broth mixture.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour remaining broth mixture and boil for a few minutes until slightly thickened.
Add cornstarch mixture and stir one minute.
Season with pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve.

title: lena culp's baked steak
directions: In skillet, melt Crisco.
Dredge pieces of steak in flour, then brown on both sides in skillet.
Salt and pepper after turning steak.
Place browned pieces in Corning or roasting pan.
When all steak is browned, add enough flour to skillet to absorb grease. Slowly pour 4 to 5 cups water (depending on amount of steak) into skillet to make gravy.
Stir constantly.
Add Kitchen Bouquet, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil; can thicken with cornstarch (mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch with a few drops of water).
Stir into boiling gravy.
Pour gravy over meat.
Cover and bake in 225° oven for 6 to 8 hours.
Will be very tender.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: hearty taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Unroll dough; press onto bottom and up sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chow mein noodles
directions: Melt chips over very low heat. Stir in noodles. Spoon onto wax paper to cool.

title: old fashion fish cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into cakes.
Bake 15 minutes to brown.
Place in broiler until golden brown.
Also, can be fried in large skillet with 2/3 cup oil.

title: orange pineapple sweet potatoes
directions: Combine orange juice, cornstarch, margarine, brown sugar and white sugar in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring, until thickened. Arrange cooked sweet potatoes and pineapple in baking dish.
Pour sauce over them.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes; uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: super bean dip
directions: Over low flame, heat beans and cream cheese until soft enough to mix.
Stir in sour cream, taco mix and Tabasco sauce.
Serve warm with chips.

title: joy's fruit salad
directions: Mix and serve cold.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Yields 1/2 gallon sauce. Must be refrigerated.
Serve with favorite seafood.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables and soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: noah's ark pudding "ashuri"
directions: Soak wheat and rice in water for 12 hours in a bowl.
In another bowl soak the dried beans and peas for 12 hours.

title: tofu and vegetable quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute the onion, green pepper, broccoli, mushrooms and corn for a few minutes.
In a blender, blend soft tofu with soy milk, basil and seasoning.
Place the sauteed vegetables in the pie shell and pour the tofu mixture over the top.
Bake until a knife inserted into the custard comes out clean (approximately 15 minutes).
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Heat sugar and margarine in pan with juice. Layer sweet potatoes in greased casserole dish; pour liquid over. Bake at 350° until heated through. Better when heated over again and again.

title: lemon lush
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and press into 10 x 10-inch ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese and 1 cup of confectioners sugar.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip and vanilla to the cream cheese mixture.
Spread on the cooled crust.
Combine pudding and cold milk and mix on low speed for approximately 2 minutes.
Spoon over cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on lemon layer and sprinkle top with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Salt and soak cucumbers overnight.
Next morning mix remaining ingredients.
Let boil; put in cucumbers and onions. Bring to a boil again, then seal in sterilized jars.

title: bertha's salsa
directions: Brown chiles and tomatoes on all sides.
Put in a brown paper bag or plastic bag until it reaches room temperature.
Peel off stems and skin and put in a bowl.
Add minced garlic, green onions and the remaining ingredients.
Hand mix and chop all ingredients together.
(Should be room temperature or chilled).

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: wonder pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a graham cracker crust.

title: chocolate peanut butter clusters
directions: Line baking sheet with waxed paper. In 2-quart microwave safe bowl, mix chocolate and peanut butter chips. Cook at Medium speed 2 minutes. Stir; cook 1 minute. Stir until melted and smooth. Add peanuts and mix. Drop mixture by 1 tablespoon onto prepared baking sheet. Let stand at room temperature until firm. Makes about 50 candies. Contains 78 calories per candy, 3 g protein, 6 g carbohydrates, 6 g fat and 0 cholesterol.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients.
Sift next 6 ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Mix well and add nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve with kaiser rolls.

title: spinach dip(club member: luke robinson)
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water. Mix other ingredients together, then add spinach. Recipe can be doubled. Serve with favorite bread or crackers.

title: cheese bread
directions: Thaw dough in bowl.
Let rise.
Roll out in a circle. Top with garlic, onions and cheese. Roll into loaf and fold ends under. Place in buttered bread pan.
Slice top diagonally.
Brush with melted butter and let rise 1
hour.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 55 minutes until brown.

title: low cholesterol muffins
directions: Mix bananas, oil, egg whites, dates and dry milk in blender. Blend until smooth and mix with dry ingredients.
Pour into 12 muffin cups and bake at 425° for 17 to 20 minutes.

title: party sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use as filling between lightly buttered slices of sandwich bread.
Trim crusts.
Cut each diagonally into 4 triangles.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone and cut into bite sized pieces.
Cook spaghetti in the chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients, chicken last and pour into casserole dishes.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot date cookies(low-fat)
directions: *To make cake flour, use 1 cup all-purpose flour minus 2 tablespoons equals 1 cup cake flour.

title: minute steaks and mushroom soup
directions: Brown steaks in margarine.
Add salt and pepper.
Turn over once.
Add mushroom soup.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes. Cover tightly while simmering.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add soup and cheese.
Add broccoli and rice.
Stir.
Place in
buttered casserole dish and bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done, about 1 hour.
Put aside 1 cup of broth.
Mix broth, soup and sour cream and beat until it makes a creamy sauce.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Layer chicken, sauce and crackers, ending with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: round steak
directions: Put round steak in crock-pot.
Pour onion soup mix and stewed tomatoes on top.
Put on low before work.
Ready to serve after 8 to 10 hours of cooking.

title: zesty french dressing
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: chicken fajitas(heart healthy)
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil.
Place in 300° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Meanwhile, spray large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Add onion and garlic; stir-fry for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add green pepper; stir-fry for 1 to 2 minutes more or until vegetable are crisp-tender.
Remove from skillet.
Add oil to skillet and add chicken; stir-fry for 3 to 5 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Add salsa.
Cook and stir until heated through.

title: easy-time holiday squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to butter in large mixing bowl, creaming at medium speed of mixer until light and fluffy.
At medium speed, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
At low speed, add flour and lemon extract.
Pour batter into well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mark off into 20 squares.
Place 1 heaping tablespoonful pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
While warm, sift powdered sugar over cake.

title: easy super supper taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together. Drain. Combine all ingredients in large pot and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve with Tostitos on top.

title: never fail beef stew
directions: Parboil the carrots and potatoes.
Combine them with the other ingredients in a crock-pot.
Add enough water to cover and mix to blend water and seasonings.
Cook on low heat until vegetables and meat are tender, approximately 5 hours.
Or place ingredients in a covered, ovenproof pot and bake in the oven at 325° for 2 to 3 hours.
Serves six.

title: delicious green beans
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook for 5 minutes after it starts to boil.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Heat 1-inch of oil in a skillet.
Mix flour and salt; add milk, oil and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Cut onions into 1/4-inch thick slices and separate into rings.
Dip each ring into batter (drain excess batter over bowl) and drop a few at a time into hot oil heated to 375°.
Cook until golden brown; drain on paper towels.
These may be cooled, wrapped and frozen.
Reheat in a 350° oven about 5 minutes.
Makes lots!!!

title: shrimp and feta cheese pasta a la grecque(low-fat)
directions: Combine shrimp, Feta, onion, oregano, tomatoes, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Let mixture stand at room temperature for at least 1 hour.
Add pasta to sauce and toss to coat, or serve sauce separately to top pasta.

title: shrimp fettuccine
directions: Melt margarine, minced onion, shrimp and seasonings.
Add cream cheese, Tabasco and Parmesan cheese; melt and mix.
Heat on medium to soft boil, stirring very frequently.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Boil noodles; rinse with hot water.
Mix with sauce.
Serve with salad and French bread.

title: baked ziti casserole
directions: Note:
Spaghetti sauce can be prepared ahead of time.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Combine meal, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add egg, milk and oil.
Pour batter into preheated, greased, 8-inch iron skillet or pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: herbed potato wedges
directions: Melt butter in a large shallow baking dish.
Arrange potatoes in single layer over butter.
Sprinkle with cheese, bacon, and seasonings.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and baste with butter.
Return to oven for 20-30 minutes till tender.
Mix chives and sour cream and serve on the side.

title: ruth e's brownies
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add syrup.
Beat in one egg at a time. Add flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Ice.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Sift and shake ingredients together 5 times to mix.
Store in airtight container and keep refrigerated.
To make cocoa, use 1/4 cup mix to each cup of water.

title: apricot salad
directions: Cook jello, pineapple and water together 10 minutes; cool. Mix cream cheese with enough juice from apricots to make it soft and creamy.
Drain and chop apricots.
Mix all ingredients; pour in a large mold or a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let set overnight.
Serves 15.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spanish punch
directions: Add sugar to hot tea.
Stir until dissolved.
Add juices. Serve over ice.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place in baking dish.
Slice onion and green pepper on top.
Mix 1/2 can milk with mushroom soup.
Pour on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into a large baking dish evenly.
Spread more ketchup over top (not heavy).
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, baking powder, pecans and salt; blend together.
Add 1 level teaspoon soda, dissolved in hot water, then flour and bananas.
Bake in ungreased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
May take longer if bananas are very ripe or according to the climate.

title: cheese ball with everything
directions: Let Swiss and Cheddar cheeses come to room temperature.
In a large mixer bowl beat together cream cheese and sour cream until fluffy.
Beat in Swiss cheese, Cheddar cheese, onion, pimiento, pickle relish, half of bacon, 1/4 cup of the pecans, salt and pepper.
Cover and chill until firm.
shape into 1 large or 2 small balls on waxed paper.
In a small bowl combine remaining bacon, pecans, parsley and poppy seed.
Turn mixture out onto clean sheet of waxed paper.
Roll cheese ball in seed mixture to coat.
Wrap and chill.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: taco pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass pan (ungreased), unroll crescent rolls and press together perforations and dough up onto sides.
Cook ground meat according to taco seasoning instructions.
Spread meat (after cooled) onto uncooked crescent rolls.
Layer on sour cream, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crescent rolls look brown.
Let cool and cut.
Serve with taco sauce or extra sour cream.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix softened butter, egg, sugar, milk and vanilla until blended.
Add flour and mix by hand.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: pan fried trout
directions: Sprinkle inside of trout with lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Combine remaining salt, flour and pepper.
Roll trout in flour mixture.
Slowly heat oil in skillet.
Saute trout 5 minutes.
Turn and saute other side 1 minute.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes, turning onion often.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients; stir.
Mix in apples and nuts.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream puff coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add 2 tablespoons cold water and mix until smooth.
Spread thinly on 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
(It will not go clear to corners.)

title: almond chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey mustard sauce and dip
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan.
Remove from heat and add cornstarch and turmeric.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Return to medium heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Mix dry jello with Cool Whip.
Drain juice of pineapple and mandarin
oranges
and
mix
with Cool Whip mixture.
Add cottage cheese
and mix well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or more and it is ready to eat.
Serves 10.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs, flour, salt, extract and syrup. Stir well; add pecans.
Pour in unbaked crust and bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Grease tube pan and pour 1/2 of the batter in.
Top with a sugar mix consisting of the last 3 ingredients combined together.
Add remaining batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Allow to stand 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Prepare chicken soup supplement according to instructions. Mix all ingredients together.
Toast 1 slice of diet bread and make into crumbs.
Place mixed ingredients into casserole and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake until very hot.

title: impossible coconut custard pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Combine all but coconut in blender.
Blend several minutes. Pour into 10-inch greased and floured pie dish or two 8-inch pans. Put coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit tea smoothie
directions: In teapot, pour boiling water over tea bags.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer 1 hour.

title: wassell
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil; then simmer. Serve hot.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl combine eggs, syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla until well blended (by hand).
Stir in pecans.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife blade inserted in middle of pie comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: In a bowl combine eggs, broccoli, corn, onion, salt, and pepper.
In a small sauce pan melt butter.
Add stuffing and mix well.
Stir 3/4 cup of stuffing mix into vegetable mixture.
Turn into an ungreased 1 qt. casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fajita rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package, omitting butter and salt. Cook and stir meat, vegetables and garlic in hot oil in large skillet until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: grammy's famous pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides and salt and pepper to taste. Place slice of onion and green pepper on top of each.
Pour rice carefully into spaces between pork chops and spoon tomatoes over rice and chops.
If dry, use small can of tomato juice over all. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw hash browns.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well together.
Pour in lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Melt marshmallows and candy bars together with 1/2 inch milk over low heat.
Stir often.
Let cool.
Pour into freezer container and finish filling freezer with milk.
Freeze.

title: ziti bake
directions: Boil ziti until tender.
Pour into baking dish. Mix cottage cheese or Ricotta cheese with sauce.
Pour over ziti.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over sauce. Bake in a 350° oven until the Mozzarella cheese melts and sauce bubbles.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients for 1 1/2 hours until tender.
Mix flour and water to make paste.
Add flour paste to other ingredients; stir and cook 10 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal. Good with hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, place 2 tablespoons of butter and microwave 1/2 to 1 minute until melted.
Add cracker crumbs and pecans.
Microwave 3 minutes.
Stir after half the time.
Set aside.

title: bumble bee bread
directions: Bring margarine, sugar and cinnamon to a boil.
Grease well a tube pan.
Quarter biscuits and drop into pan.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: *Or use 1 bouillon cube dissolved in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.

title: tennessee style pork barbecue
directions: Any large cut of pork will do, but picnic, Boston butt or shoulder is preferred.
Remove skin and almost all visible fat.

title: ember's peas and peanuts salad
directions: 1st Layer:
1 medium head lettuce, shredded.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and add beans.
Cook cheese soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes until cheese has melted.
In large bowl, tear lettuce as for a salad.
Add sliced onion, mixed in ground beef and beans. Add cheese and tomato mixture.
Crush taco chips in bag and add to salad; toss.
Serves 4 to 6
people.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Add all remaining ingredients. Let simmer 1 to 2 hours. You'll probably need to add more water as it cooks. Serve in bowls topped with grated cheese or crushed tortilla chips and cornbread.

title: my zucchini bread
directions: Chop walnuts; set aside.
Grate zucchini; set aside.
Beat the eggs in mixing bowl until frothy.
Add sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Pour in alternately with zucchini. Add nuts.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured loaf pans (8 x 4 x 3-inch) and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix beef, sausage, bread and egg. Add onions, Italian seasonings and garlic powder. Mix well.
Roll into golf ball size balls. Pour tomato sauce into deep pan; add bay leaf or two. Add meatballs and cook for 2 hours.
Serve over noodles. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Use juice from cherries and pineapple; heat for dissolving jello.
Dissolve jello.
Add Coca Colas to this.
Allow to congeal slightly and then add broken cream cheese, cherries and pineapples. Nuts if used.
Place in molds.
Allow to congeal.
Remove from molds and serve on lettuce.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt half of the margarine in casserole.
Put onion in and top with soup.
Spread cornflake crumbs over this and dot with remaining margarine.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese for a crowd
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Add cheeses, green pepper, onion, and pimentos.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni mixture and mix well.
Pour into two greased 13x9 baking dishes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until bubbly and browned.

title: quick-to-fix-quesadilla
directions: In cast-iron skillet stack tortillas with cheese and peppers in between, ending with cheese and peppers on top; cover.
Place on embers of campfire or on grill rack above medium coals.
Cook 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut into 6 to 8 wedges.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: simple cream cheese icing
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine, vanilla and powdered sugar well with a mixer on high speed until smooth.
Excellent for carrot cake or red velvet cake.

title: orange puff
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and congeal (cool) in long glass dish. Mix last 3 ingredients well and spread on top of congealed salad.

title: grilled eggplant salad
directions: Slice eggplant lengthwise about 1/4-inch thick (skin optional).
Brush with olive oil.
Brown on gas grill both sides about 5 minutes each side.
Put on serving platter and cover with thinly sliced Vidalia onions.
Next layer with thinly sliced tomatoes.
Crumble Feta cheese generously on top.
Sprinkle balsamic vinegar on top.
Serve immediately.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat the sugar and salad oil until fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Beat in the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in small pans.

title: diabetic banana pudding
directions: Premix whipped topping according to package directions. Premix pudding
according
to
package directions.
Layer 1/2 graham cracker
crumbs in bottom of dish.	Slice 3 bananas and add
1/2 pudding
mixture and 1/2 whipped topping.
Alternate with
crumbs, bananas
and pudding; top with whipped topping. Chill several hours before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 300° for one hour.

title: spaghetti bread
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Put cooked spaghetti in a casserole dish and cover with egg-milk mixture.
Pour spaghetti sauce over spaghetti and layer with sliced mushrooms.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with 3 cups Mozzarella cheese over top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: breakfast puff
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
In a large skillet over medium heat, melt margarine; add fruit and cook until softened.
Apples take about 10 minutes.
Stir in 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Arrange sauteed fruit in pie plate and set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter; coat the stuffing.
Put layer in bottom of casserole.
Reserve 1/2 for topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In
a
large
bowl, cream margarine and sugar together. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add egg, water and vanilla; beat well.
Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and
nutmeg
together
and
add
to creamed mixture, mixing well. Stir
in
oats and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until
lightly browned.
Let
cool
slightly on cookie sheets before moving to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, flour and milk on low heat, stirring often until mixture thickens.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese until evenly colored. Add oranges and crushed pineapple. Gently fold in Cool Whip.

title: landfill cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch or jelly roll pan. Prepare pudding as directed.
Cut the cake into 1-inch squares and put 1/2 into a large bowl.
Spread 1/2 of the pudding over the cake, then 1/2 of the Cool Whip over the pudding and sprinkle with 1/2 of the candy.
Repeat the layers.

title: marble squares
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat.
Add dry ingredients and stir.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes, then swish with fork and bake 15 minutes more.
Test with toothpick.
Do not overbake.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut chipped beef into small pieces.
Cut up green part of onions.
Add this in bowl and mix cream cheese, garlic and Worcestershire sauce together with a fork until well blended. Refrigerate.
When chilled, about 1/2 hour, you can make into a ball.
Serve on any favorite cracker.

title: tempura dipping sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and serve on the side with grated dikon and ginger.

title: strawberry blossoms
directions: Remove stems from the berries, forming a flat base.
Place berries on a plate, pointed end up.
With a sharp knife, carefully make 6 evenly spaced cuts to within a quarter inch of the base (be careful not to slice through the base).
Pull petals slightly apart.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar and sour cream until fluffy. Using a pastry bag or small spoon, fill the strawberry flowers with the cream cheese mixture.
Use as a garnish or mini dessert.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Combine ground beef with rice, egg, onion, carrot, salt, garlic salt, pepper, garlic and parsley; set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Marinate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Stir several times.

title: rocha candy
directions: Have ready a good sized cookie sheet (non-stick).
Have everything ready as this cooks fast.
Grind walnuts to fine crumb stage.
Boil first 4 ingredients to a hard ball stage.
It will be a caramel color.
Stir constantly.
Test a drop or 2 of cooking mixture in cold water.
When done, work fast.
Pour out on cookie sheet and spread as far as you can.
Sprinkle milk chocolate chips on and let melt.
Top with nuts.
Next day when hard, spread with more melted chips and nuts.
Keeps well.
Yummy!

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Mix and stir all ingredients together.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: kay's crawfish fettucine
directions: Melt butter, saute chopped onions, bell pepper and celery. Add garlic, parsley and crawfish.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add flour, half and half,
and cheese.
After cheese melts, cook on low about 20 minutes.
Cook noodles and toss with crawfish mixture.
Place in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: onion bake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Put small amount of soup on bottom of dish.
Layer slices of French bread, sliced onions and Swiss cheese.
Top with golden mushroom soup.
Repeat steps until full.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour and then 20 minutes uncovered.

title: vegetable-bean stew with couscous
directions: In a small pan, combine olive oil or salad oil, ground red pepper (cayenne), ground cumin, garlic and salt.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring, until ingredients are well blended (5 minutes).
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: raisin cream pie(2 crusts)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix flour and sugar together before adding to other mixture.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Cover with crust.
Brush lightly with mixture left in bowl.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato-broccoli soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large Dutch oven. Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat. Simmer 20 minutes. Combine milk and flour, stirring until smooth. Add milk mixture and cheese to vegetable mixture in Dutch oven. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts and mixture thickens. If desired, sprinkle with crushed red pepper. Makes 7 (1 cup) servings.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips and 14 ounces of the almond bark in a large saucepan, stirring constantly.
When smooth, remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts, mixing well.
Pour onto a greased 12-inch round metal pizza pan.
Top with cherries while still warm.
Melt remaining white almond bark and drizzle randomly over "Chocolate Pizza." Chill until firm.

title: beef and broccoli bake
directions: Mix flour, milk and cream cheese. Add egg and seasonings.
Mix with meat and broccoli.
Place in a 9 or 10-inch pie pan or long baking dish.
Cut Monterey Jack cheese and put on top of mixture. Flatten crescent rolls and place on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: chili rice balls
directions: Mix preceding ingredients and make into meat balls.
Fry in oil until brown.
Drain oil to 1/4 cup.
Add 2 (8 oz.) cans tomato sauce, 2 cans water, and 4 tbsp. bar-b-que sauce.
Simmer about 45 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Cream cheeses together, add beef and onions.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 400°.
Top will brown.
Add pecans, raisins and miniature marshmallows the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Combine next 7 ingredients and mix with hash browns.
Put all in a 3-quart casserole, 12 x 13-inch or 13 x 15-inch.
Saute cornflakes in butter and sprinkle on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: irish stew
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Using a 5 to 6-quart Dutch oven, mix tomatoes, wine, broth, tapioca, sugar, Italian seasoning, salt, bay leaves and pepper.
Stir in the beef.
Add carrots, celery and onions.
Cover and bake about 3 hours, stirring twice.
Add mushrooms and mustard.
Bake another 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: oven barbecue spareribs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put ribs on rack in pan and roast 45 minutes.
Combine sugar and spices in saucepan, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Pour 1/3 of sauce over ribs and roast 30 minutes longer.
Turn ribs and pour 1/2 remaining sauce over them, roast 1 hour longer until fully cooked, brush with rest of sauce several times.

title: tuna tomato wich
directions: In skillet, cook green pepper in butter until tender.
Add soup, water and tuna.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Add tomato wedges.
Heat.
Serve on toast.
Garnish with onion.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: salted peanut chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a large bowl, combine all crust ingredients (except marshmallows) on low speed until crumbly.
Press firmly into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Immediately sprinkle with marshmallows. Return to oven for 1 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows just begin to puff.
Cool while preparing topping.

title: dieter's juice
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: easy clam dip
directions: Drain clams (reserve juice).
Combine all ingredients except clam juice and crackers.
Blend.
Gradually add about 2 tablespoons clam juice.
Beat.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add celery, onions, soups and water. Add rice. Mix.
Pour in ungreased casserole (3-quart).
Heat oven to 325°. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
(I use 10-inch casserole.)
Top with chopped cashews or I use chow mein noodles.

title: batter for shrimp or chicken
directions: Salt and pepper shrimp or chicken; mix ingredients and let batter chill for best results.
Dip shrimp or chicken into batter and deep fry.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Add ham, cheese, onions and white pepper.
Mix to distribute ingredients evenly.
Pour mixture into 10-inch raw pie shell. Cook approximately 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into cooked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli. Saute onions and celery in oleo. Add soup and milk and heat for about 3 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz, broccoli, rice, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Put in covered casserole coated with Pam.
Sprinkle parmesan cheese over top.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Remove lid for last 10 minutes.

title: fideo
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain excess fat and set aside. Heat oil and brown Fideo noodles until medium to dark brown; set aside.
In a large pot, combine tomato sauce, whole tomatoes, spices and potatoes; mix well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and add meat mixture and noodles.
Simmer slowly about 1 hour.
Add additional water if needed.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla in a medium mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Add eggs and beat until thoroughly blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in a pastry shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple - carrot jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice plus 2 Tbsp. vinegar or 2 Tbsp. (scant) lemon juice plus 1/2 water after boiling water stirred into lemon Jello.
Then add above ingredients soon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form ball.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Chill. Serves about 30.

title: chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to room temperature. Cream sugar with cream cheese, vanilla, and milk. Spoon into pie crust. Make Jell- O pie mix according to directions. Pour chocolate pie mix on top of cream cheese. Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo syrup and water in a large pan.
Cook over medium heat until it becomes brittle and breaks when dropped in cold water.
Add peanuts and cook until peanuts begin to pop. Remove from heat and add butter, baking soda and vanilla.
Stir and pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: peach crisp(microwave)
directions: Arrange peaches in an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Melt margarine in glass bowl 45 to 60 seconds on High.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in a bowl.
Add melted butter and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over peaches. Cook uncovered 7 to 8 minutes on High. rotate dish 1 quarter turn once.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat with garlic, onion and A.1. sauce in a large pan. Add potatoes, stewed tomatoes and chili salsa.
Add sufficient amount of water to completely cover contents.
Simmer on medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice or can be used as burrito mix.

title: basil pesto
directions: Process fresh basil leaves and remaining ingredients in a food processor until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides. Store pesto in refrigerator up to 5 days.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Add butter to hot eggplant; mix until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° until center rises, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken or turkey, celery, soup, mixed vegetables, broth or 1/3 cup cooking oil and finish the 1 1/2 cups with water.
Pour into Pyrex dish (a long one).
Melt margarine; mix with Bisquick and milk.
Do not stir.
Cook at 400° for 1 hour.

title: sugared bacon
directions: Beat brown sugar, egg yolks, Worcester sauce and mustard until well blend.
Dip bacon into mixture and roll in crumbs. Place bacon on a broiler pan.
Bake in a preheated 250° oven for 20 minutes or until brown and crispy.

title: quickie beef dinner
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Stir in beef broth, water, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and return to boil.
Cover and cook until macaroni is tender.

title: warm spinach and cheddar dip
directions: In 1-quart casserole dish, combine soup, sour cream, spinach and 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: angel food cake
directions: Fold pineapple with juice in cake mix. Pour in tube pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans and vanilla, in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
When mixture comes to a boil, add pecans and cook until it reaches 234° or until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Yield: about 24 pieces.

title: gloria's pineapple cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In another bowl, add butter and sugar together; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend well.
Alternately blend milk and flour mixture into butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Add lemon extract.
Beat well.
Fold in pineapple before pouring batter into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set temperature to 350° and bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes. While cake is baking, mix together 2 tablespoons butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar and crushed pineapple.
Pour on cake.
Place on plate and serve warm.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients and fry in deep fat.

title: snowball cake
directions: Cut cake in bite size and place 1/2 in pan.
Soften cream cheese.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Mix Dream Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Put part of mixture over first half of the angel food cake.
Then add other half of cake.
Spread with rest of mixture.
Then spread cherry pie filling on top.

title: seafood spread
directions: Flake crab meat and shrimp.
Mix with remaining ingredients, except potato chips.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry filled french toast
directions: Spread cream cheese on 6 slices bread.
Spread jam over cheese.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Cut diagonally to form triangles.
Beat together eggs, milk, vanilla and nutmeg in a shallow bowl.
Set aside.
Place margarine in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Place under broiler until margarine is melted.
Dip each triangle in egg mixture and place on melted batter in baking pan.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat, 2 to 3 minutes per side, or until golden brown.
Serve with syrup.

title: vanilla treats
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla, then sifted dry ingredients.
Press on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy biscuit lasagne
directions: Cook beef and onion in 4-quart saucepan; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, 1 tablespoon parsley flakes and oregano.
Heat to boiling. Mix remaining ingredients, except zucchini and Mozzarella cheese, until dough forms.
Spread 1/2 of the dough in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 zucchini, 1/2 meat mixture and 1/2 Mozzarella over dough.
Drop rest of dough by spoonfuls over cheese.
Repeat layers of zucchini, meat and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 32 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken-taco casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Reserve 1 cup broth.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Combine chicken, sauce, soup, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Line a greased baking dish with part of corn chips.
Add chicken mixture, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover with remaining corn chips.
Add broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ritz mints cookies
directions: Melt the chocolate in a double boiler or microwave. Stir in 6 or 7 drops of peppermint oil. Coat both sides of a cracker and place on wax paper to dry. This will remind you of thin mint cookies.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Melt 1/2 cube butter; stir in 2 large tablespoons flour, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon (preferably).
Add 1 to 1 1/2 cups milk; stir over low heat to make the white sauce creamy. Add salt and pepper to taste after you take off the stove.
Saute the peppers and onions in a little butter or water until tender; cover.
Beat the egg and add drained onions, peppers, drained corn and add the white sauce.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle a few bread crumbs over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 4 to 5.

title: spicy chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boiling; simmer until thick as wanted, about 1 to 2 hours.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Pour, boiling hot, into hot jars, leaving 1/8-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process in hot water bath 15 minutes. Yields about 8 pints.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown beef and chopped onions.
Drain and add cabbage and water.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes slowly.
Add pinto beans, tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes more.

title: chicken broth with cilantro wontons(thailand)
directions: Cut the chicken breast into small pieces, then chop medium-fine with a cleaver or large knife.
Combine in a bowl with the sliced cilantro, soy sauce, salt, pepper and ground red pepper to taste. Place about 1 teaspoon of the chicken mixture on each of the wonton skins.
Paint the edges with the flour mixture and fold to form a neat triangle.
