Paint the two points of the triangle that are farthest apart, then paste together to form a bishop's hat shape. Clean the carrot, leek, celery and turnip, then cut into fine julienne.
You should have a total of about 1 1/2 cups.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Combine soda, flour, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine shortening, white sugar and brown sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Stir in chips. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until light brown.

title: crab newberg
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add flour, salt, nutmeg and cayenne.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Gradually add 1/2 cup hot sauce mixture to egg yolks, beating to blend.
Add egg mixture to remaining sauce mixture.
Mix well.
Add crab and liquid.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes, until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in sherry.
Serve over hot rice.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Over low heat, cook butter, brown sugar and water. Stir in chocolate chips and stir
until smooth.
Pour into a large mixing bowl and cool 10 minutes.
Using a mixer, beat in eggs, one at a time. Reduce speed and mix in flour, soda and salt.
Chill dough 1 hour.

title: candied citrus peel
directions: Put 2 cups of peel in a saucepan, cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes.
Drain. Repeat cooking twice.
Wash saucepan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix 3 kinds of soups (undiluted) with rice and water chestnuts.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and place raw chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt or any kind of seasoning you wish.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.

title: pie dough
directions: Add flour and then shortening.
On
the side, mix egg, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Mix in large bowl, using large roasting fork.
Roll into ball.
Do not knead.

title: coconut macaroons(drop cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Remove immediately. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: cheesy spinach dip
directions: Range top directions:
Place cheese in a 2-quart saucepan. Heat over low heat, stirring frequently until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat about 5 minutes longer, stirring occasionally until warm.
Makes about 3 cups dip.
Serve with bagels snack.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake layers; cool completely.
Prepare instant pudding according to directions on package; refrigerate.
Place one cake layer in bottom of 6-quart punch bowl.
Add in layers 1/2 of ingredients in the following order:
prepared pudding, cherry pie filling, fruit cocktail, crushed pineapple, nuts, coconut and Cool Whip.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Beat together until creamy.
Serve with fruits as a dip.
Keep refrigerated.
Can be used as a dressing for fruit salad.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix soups and mixed vegetables in skillet and bring to a boil. Place chicken in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over chicken.

title: fresh fruit frozen squares
directions: Mix crust ingredients in shallow pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Add apples and nuts, then add raisins and mix into batter by hand.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Frost with simple frosting.

title: apple crunch muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until fine crumbs form.
Combine milk and egg.
Add dry ingredients along with apples.
Stir just to moisten.
Spoon batter into muffin cups filling 2/3 full.
Mix together topping and sprinkle on top of muffin batter.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Slowly add water and vinegar.
Add raisins and cook slowly over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cook 10 minutes longer to plump raisins, then add butter.
Serve as a sauce to use on ham.

title: oatmeal fudge cookies
directions: In a saucepan, cook sugar, cocoa, milk and butter. Boil for 3 minutes, then remove from heat. Pour over oatmeal and peanut butter, which you measured into a separate bowl. Mix good for about a minute. Drop by spoon onto waxed paper and let dry. (Cool.)

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook ground
beef
in
a
large
skillet or Dutch oven, stirring until
crumbled
into
small pieces and well browned. Add onion
and
garlic to meat; cook about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add
tomatoes
to skillet and chop into bite size chunks.
Stir
in
kidney beans (drain liquid from can first), chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add cayenne pepper if you like it hot.
Reduce heat to simmering and cook, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix with melted margarine.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix pudding and milk with electric mixer until thick.
Add ice cream; mix well and pour over crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top, then sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.

title: chocolate sheet
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Put next 3 ingredients on stove and bring to boil.
Add to first mixture.
Pour into 10 x 15-inch cookie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil milk, butter and sugar.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well and form into small balls.
Yield - 4 doz. cookies.

title: plum or peach kuchen
directions: Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve hot with cream.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water until tender.
Brown ground beef. Add onion and pepper and cook until tender.
Layer ground beef, noodles, tomato sauce and cream of mushroom soup.
Place in casserole, sprayed with Pam.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes. Remove from oven and place cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Cook chicken or turkey and chop.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour into casserole dish. Bake 15 minutes in a 375° oven or until bubbly.
Add 1 can chow mein noodles and sprinkle on top during last few minutes of baking.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots for 5 minutes (slice first).
Cool.
Layer with onion and green pepper.
Bring to boil soup, sugar, vinegar, salad oil, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over cooled vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep 10 days if kept refrigerated.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef.
Add onions, garlic, sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add chocolate syrup, flour and rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in an oblong pan.

title: one dish breakfast
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Seal all seams and curl up edges slightly. Pour over rolls the drained and cooked sausage, then uncooked hash browns, beaten eggs and cheese. Season to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: peachy meatballs
directions: Make meatballs as you would meat loaf.
Make balls.
Cook in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. For sauce, use chili sauce and peach preserves. Warm until boiling. Add meatballs; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chunky tomato cheese pie
directions: Cut 4 tomatoes into cubes (4 cups).
Slice other tomato; set aside.
Combine tomato cubes, bread crumbs, flour, sugar and salt; toss until mixed.
Place in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove; garnish with tomato and cheese slices.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: seafood creole
directions: Prepare roux by melting margarine in a large skillet.
Over medium heat, blend in flour and stir constantly until roux is dark brown.
Do not scorch!
Stir reserved tomato liquid and water to equal 1 cup.
Stir into roux and blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients except fish, shrimp and rice.
Cook and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp or fish and simmer 10 minutes. Remove bay leaves and serve with rice.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Plump raisins in hot water; drain.
Mix with apples, celery and walnuts.
Blend salad dressing with lemon juice and mix lightly with raisin/apple mixture.
Serve in cups lined with lettuce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Place 2/3 of the crushed cookies on bottom of 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Whip cream cheese with margarine.
Add Cool Whip then milk.
Add pudding and whip until all mixed together.
Put mixture on top of crushed Oreos.
Complete with remaining Oreo toppings!

title: johnny cake
directions: Mix the dry ingredients. Cut in the shortening. Add the milk all at once. Stir until moistened. Pour into a greased 8 x 8 inch pan. Bake at 350° for
30-35 minutes. This is good to eat with soup.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; add seasoning to taste.
Drain meat.
In casserole dish, place Tater Tots, meat and soup.
Mix together. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix butter with cornflake crumbs.
Mix together other ingredients and add a touch of milk for a little moisture.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: elaine burkett's egg custard
directions: Mix
sugar
and
flour;
add
eggs, milk, flavoring and butter.
Pour
into 9-inch pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until center is firm.

title: chicken, sausage and rice casserole
directions: Remove skin from sausage and cut into bite-size pieces.
Saute with onions, celery and bell pepper until tender.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix rice, sausage, chicken and seasonings together.
Grease casserole dish with margarine; add mixture and pour cream of mushroom over mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple whip
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, cornstarch and pineapple juice and cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour cooled mixture over pineapple and marshmallows.
Add Cool Whip.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple. Reserve 3 tablespoons juice. Combine sugar, flour and juice. Add cheese and pineapple. Stir well. Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole dish. Combine butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over pineapple mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: garlic green beans
directions: After snapping ends of green beans and breaking in half, put into pot.
Just cover with water and add butter and garlic salt to taste.
Boil until beans change color slightly; drain and serve.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and shortening well.
Add tomato soup and water to above and mix well.
Add dry ingredients to above and mix well.
Add raisins and/or nuts.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven in a standard size loaf pan.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: *You can use precooked ham and it doesn't take as long to cook.

title: potato casserole
directions: Take potatoes.
Peel, cube and soak in water 15 minutes. Drain.
Put in a buttered casserole.
Dot with butter.
Take dressing.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Cover.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Stir and bake until done, usually 45 to 60 minutes. Delicious!

title: quick cocoa cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, oleo and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for about 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from the fire and quickly add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix well and spoon out onto waxed paper.

title: easy cheesy spaghetti
directions: Brown meat with onion, pepper and garlic.
Add the soups and water.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
Add the cheese, salt and pepper and stir until the cheese is melted.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Drain well and add to the meat mixture. Put into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with more cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice, until cucumber is tender-crisp and onion is translucent.
Put into hot, sterilized jars.
Cover; cool slightly and refrigerate.

title: sweet pepper soup
directions: Cook peppers and onion in olive oil in large Dutch oven over medium high heat, stirring constantly until tender.
Cool slightly. Place about 1/4 of mixture into electric blender.
Add 1/2 cup broth and process until smooth.
Pour mixture through wire mesh strainer into large bowl, discarding pulp.
Repeat procedure 3 times with remaining pepper mixture and 1 1/2 cups broth.
Return pepper mixture, remaining broth, salt and curry powder to Dutch oven.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low, simmer 15 minutes.
Cool.
Using a wire whisk, stir in buttermilk.
Cover and chill.
Serve cold.
Yields 12 cups.

title: italian cookies
directions: Melt butter or margarine; cool.
Beat eggs, flavorings and sugar until light.
Add cooled butter or margarine and mix well. Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture; mix by hand.
Test dough.
If too sticky to handle, add extra flour and baking powder.
For every cup of flour needed, use 1 teaspoon baking powder (don't add too much flour or they will be tough).

title: butter pecan brownies
directions: Pour into cake pan and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coffee lopez
directions: In a heat-proof pitcher, combine all ingredients except the whipped cream.
Mix well.
Pour into mugs; top with whipped cream. Serve immediately.
Makes 5 cups.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with butter, then cool.
Beat eggs and salt until light.
Gradually add sifted sugar.
Beat until light and creamy.
Fold in the melted mixture and 1 teaspoon of vanilla. Sift and add flour.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in pecans.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 inch pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 325°
for 30 minutes.
When COLD, cut in squares.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees (250 degrees if using a glass pan).
Mix crushed pretzels with 3 tsp. sugar and butter and spread in a greased 9 x 13 in. pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool. Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping. Spread to edge of dish on top of pretzel layer.
Dissolve Jello in water in a bowl.
Add strawberries.
Mix well and put in refrigerator until thickened.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate until firm and ready to serve.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in double boiler.
Cook until thick, then add butter.
Very good for potato salad.

title: fennel and chicken salad
directions: Trim stems from fennel and peel bottoms.
Chop 1 tablespoon of the fronds; set aside.
Chop bulbs and combine with chicken and shallots.
Beat mayonnaise with mustard and Pernod until smooth. Add chicken mixture, salt and pepper to taste and garnish with fronds.

title: creole shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 3 tablespoons oil until tender. Add okra and tomatoes. Make a dark roux using 6 tablespoons flour and 6 tablespoons oil. Add 2 quarts water to roux. Stir constantly. Combine all ingredients except for shrimp. Cook on medium heat for 2 hours. Add shrimp and crabmeat. Cook until pink. Serves 8 to 10.

title: window pane cake
directions: Melt in double boiler, chocolate and butter.
Beat egg, add to chocolate.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Blend in marshmallows gently, but not over heat.
Don't let marshmallows melt.
Form a log and roll in coconut and nuts, if you wish.
Wrap in foil. Freeze.
It's easier to cut if frozen.

title: broiled beef with mushroom stuffing
directions: Dice ham slices.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, melt butter or margarine; add mushrooms, ham, green onions, salt and pepper; cook until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently. Remove from heat.
Add bread cubes and water; toss gently to mix well; set aside.

title: chicken yummy
directions: Split, skin and bone chicken; arrange in shallow baking pan. Top each with a piece of cheese.
Stir soup and water together and spoon on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing and drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position in oven; preheat oven to 425°. Combine pie filling with 1/2 teaspoon lemon rind.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then eggs, ReaLemon juice, vanilla and remaining 1/2 teaspoon lemon rind.
Spoon over blueberries.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Bake 25 minutes or until set.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Cut biscuits in 1/4 pieces and mix in sugar mixture a few at a time.
Line bottom of Bundt pan with pecans and layer biscuits, pecans and raisins.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water, stirring until transparent. Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Mix well until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Stir occasionally until cool or put in refrigerator for about 1/2 hour.

title: artichoke hearts
directions: Boil and drain artichoke hearts according to package directions.
Mix them with the olives, mushrooms and bread crumbs in a Corning Ware bowl.
Pour olive oil over and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tennessee hillbilly cake
directions: Boil sugar, raisins, water, margarine, allspice and cinnamon in heavy saucepan for one minute, then add flour, soda and salt. Pour on a cookie sheet and bake until center tests done.

title: barbecued zucchini
directions: Place in double or heavy-duty foil.
Wrap securely and place on coals 14 to 16 minutes.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Combine croutons and Cheddar cheese.
Spread in bottom of greased 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Mix eggs, milk, salt, mustard, onion powder and pepper until well blended.
Pour over crouton mixture.
Spread bacon on top of casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until eggs are set.
Garnish with bacon curls if desired.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
In stew pot combine with all other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour batter into a greased Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done. Sprinkle additional pecans on top. Do not remove cake from pan. Add glaze.

title: corn au gratin
directions: In the bottom of a very lightly greased glass baking dish, place a layer of crushed soda crackers.
Pour a can of drained whole kernel corn over the soda crackers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place
margarine or butter over the corn.
Have butter broken in small bits and spread evenly over the corn.
Sprinkle grated cheese (sharp Cheddar) over all.
Then add another layer of finely crushed soda cracker crumbs. Pour enough milk over all to cover all ingredients in dish.
Bake in a 325°
oven until firm and slightly browned.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Sprinkle pecans and coconut in the bottom of greased cake pan. Mix cake mix, using directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Blend together sugar and cream cheese.
Add milk.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar, water, pineapple juice, orange juice and lemonade.
Stir.
Before serving, add 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: luisa's pico de gallo
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and heat through.
Serve warm in a chafing dish or hollowed out round bread loaf, using bread chunks or crackers for dipping.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Blend together walnuts, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 egg whites; set aside.
Sift together flour and 3 tablespoons sugar into mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Blend together egg yolks and 3 tablespoons milk.
Add liquid to flour mixture, stirring until flour is moistened.
Add more milk if necessary to make a soft dough.
Turn
out onto lightly floured board; divide in half.
Roll out each half to 1/16-inch thick. Cut out circles with floured 3-inch cutter.
Drop 1 teaspoonful walnut mixture in center of each circle.
Fold in half; seal edges.
Place on greased baking sheets and shape into crescents. Brush tops with egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: peanut butter and butterscotch candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch morsels over hot (not boiling) water.
Add the chow mein noodles and spoon out on a dish or pan.
Cool.

title: sandy's easy peanut brittle
directions: Line a 9-inch cake pan with foil and butter thoroughly. Bring ingredients to a boil in a 10-inch skillet (not nonstick). Stir constantly. Boil until mixture turns golden brown (at least 6 minutes). Stir constantly. Quickly spread candy in pan. Cool, then peel off foil. Break into pieces.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Put Karo and sugar in
pan
and
bring	to a boil using medium heat.
Add peanut	butter	and
corn
flakes.
Put
in greased 13 x 8-inch pan and cut in squares when cool.

title: ants on a log
directions: Cover celery with peanut butter. Sprinkle with raisins.

title: cool and easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping (reserving enough for garnish
on pie if desired) until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm. Garnish with whipped topping if desired. Yield: 8 servings.

title: venison steaks
directions: Mix flour, salt and marjoram; rub over meat.
Brown steaks in hot fat in pressure pan.
Add vegetables and broth; cover and cook at 10 pound pressure 20 to 30 minutes or as manufacturer directs. Cool normally 5 minutes, then place pan under cold water to reduce pressure quickly.
Thicken liquid for gravy by rubbing vegetables through sieve, food mill or blender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick hamburger dinner
directions: Put on heavy-duty aluminum foil in layers as listed and wrap up.
Bake at 350° until meat and vegetables are done.

title: pimento casserole
directions: Grind peppers and onion.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve one package peach jello in peach juice plus water to make 1 cup hot liquid.
Add ice cream.
Pour into mold and let set.
Place peaches on first layer.
Dissolve remaining package peach jello in 2 cups hot water.
When cool, pour clear jello on top.
Let set.

title: nancy's apple pound cake
directions: Mix apples with 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside for about 1 hour.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and fold in apples.
Chopped nuts may be added if desired.
Bake in greased pan for 1 hour and 5 minutes at 350°.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef with salt, pepper, onion and bell pepper, then drain.
Add tomato sauce and oregano and pour into crust.
Beat egg well and add milk, dry mustard and cheese.
Pour over hamburger mixture and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Remove skin from tomatoes.
Chop peppers, onion and hot peppers in blender.
Chop up tomatoes and other ingredients.
Boil until 1/2 is gone.
It's ready.

title: ruglach(cream cheese pastries)
directions: Sift flour and salt in bowl.
Work in the margarine and cream cheese until you have a smooth dough.
Roll out on floured board and chill overnight.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out dough to 1/8-inch thick; cut in 4-inch squares.
Mix egg white, walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Spread one tablespoon on each square.
Roll up like a crescent and bake for 20 minutes.

title: layered pudding delight
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with whole graham crackers, breaking crackers if necessary.

title: della's hash brown casserole(her family's favorite)
directions: Place frozen potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; pour 1/3 cup of butter over potatoes.
Mix soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Spread over potatoes.
Mix crushed corn flakes with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Top potatoes with this.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cornbread
directions: Saute vegetables in 2 teaspoons margarine; add to bread crumbs and mix well.
Put 1/2 of mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with chicken.
Mix together soup and broth.
Pour over chicken and cover with rest of bread mixture.
Press mixture down firmly
and let set for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit delight
directions: Combine butter and crumbs.
Spread in cake pan or pie pan. Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package and set aside.
Combine sugar and cream cheese.
Add Dream Whip and blend.
Spread over graham crackers and top with cherry pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water, sugar, pineapple syrup and lemon juice together.
Add celery, pineapple and nuts.
Put in small mold and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease off.
Add beans.
Add tomato sauce, water and chili seasoning mix.
Mix all together and bring to a boil.
When it starts to boil, reduce heat to simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and line bottom of a casserole dish.
Boil chicken breasts until tender and place on top of broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup; spread over the chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt butter and combine with cracker crumbs.
Spread crumbs on top of the casserole.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: mrs. jessie's potato soup
directions: Fry bacon and saute onion in grease for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour grease off and add potatoes and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in soup, sour cream and gradually add milk.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Heat until hot, but do not boil.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix together the pineapple and juice, baking soda and egg. Fold in flour, sugar and chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Mix together and pour over chicken.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake for 2 hours at 350° in a Pyrex dish.
Makes enough for 1 package of chicken wings or drummettes.

title: fruit and nut cake
directions: Use dark raisins, nuts (walnuts), extra cherries and mixed fruit.
(You can use dates or currants.)

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Drain liquid from tuna.
Add bread crumbs, wheat germ, salt and pepper to tuna and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into 8 croquettes.
Roll gently in extra wheat germ.
Place on a foil-lined cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, stirring constantly, melt oleo and chocolate over very low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 50 minutes or until filling is firm in center.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine.
Add to hot water to taste.

title: victorian cookies
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter until smooth and light. Beat in lemon rind.
Combine flour and sugar.
Stir in half of the flour mixture to creamed mixture, blending well.
Stir in remaining flour.
Roll dough out onto a lightly floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 2-inch rounds.
Spoon 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon of preserves in center of each round.
Form to a triangle by folding in three edges.
Pinch edges gently.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool cookies for a few minutes.
Remove to a rack to complete cooling.
Store in a tin.

title: nut bars
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and 1/2 cup margarine and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt syrup, chips and 2 tablespoons butter over low heat and spread over crust.
Add mixed nuts over the top and press into caramel.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Cool.
Fold in de menthe, creme de cacao and Cool Whip.
Put into crust and freeze.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup and milk and heat.
Layer potatoes alternately with the soup mixture and salt and pepper each layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain grease.
Top with choice of sauce and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: apples and cheese
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Add sugar and flour.
Place apples in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread cheese mixture over top and bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.
This recipe can be made and frozen before baking.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and fill prepared pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked beans(microwave)
directions: Combine onion, catsup, mustard and brown sugar in a deep, 2-quart, non-metallic casserole.
Heat, uncovered, in microwave oven 4 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add beans.
Stir to thoroughly combine.
Top with bacon pieces.
Heat, covered, in microwave oven 12 to 15 minutes or until beans are hot and bacon has finished cooking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: scrumdiddlyumptious pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs, then add the buttermilk and follow with the remaining ingredients, blending until smooth.
Add water if batter needs thinning.
Pour on hot griddle.

title: *baked green beans with bean sprouts
directions: Put vegetables in a quart casserole in layers in this order: green beans, bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Dot with butter, salt and pepper.
Add the undiluted cream of celery soup and sprinkle on cheese.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover and spread on onion rings.
Bake 10 minutes more, uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: walnut cherry cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package, adding vanilla and 3/4 cup medium chopped walnuts.
Bake in two 9-inch layer pans.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert out onto wire racks until cool.
Fold food coloring into topping on outer edge of each layer.
Spoon pie filling in center of each.
Stack layers on serving plate.
Spread remaining topping on sides of cake.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup coarsely chopped walnuts on top of cake.
Chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add eggs and a little bit of milk to blend well. Add remaining milk, blending well. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Take off heat and add vanilla.
Line a bowl with wafers and bananas. Pour pudding over that and garnish with wafers.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Boil rice.
Mix together all ingredients and bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cold avocado soup
directions: Peel avocados and force through a sieve.
Combine with cold consomme.
Add seasonings to taste.
Divide among six consomme cups and top each serving with sour cream.

title: pineapple cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in undrained pineapple, cranberry sauce and wine.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Fold in pecans and turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
When gelatin is set, soften cheese and gradually beat in sour cream until mixture is smooth and creamy. Spread over gelatin.
Chill.
Makes about 9 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham - slow cooker
directions: Layer potatoes, ham and onions in pot.
In a small bowl, combine soup and 1 can water.
Pour over layers in pot.
Cover and cook on low until done.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: prevention pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs with margarine.
Press into 9-inch pan.
Bake crust 7 minutes.
Leave oven at 350°.
Mix all and bake 40 minutes.

title: oven stuffed cabbage
directions: Cut core out of cabbage.
Boil cabbage and keep removing outer leaves as they get a little soft.
Save remaining small pieces of cabbage.
Fry bacon and save drippings.

title: cherry-pecan pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat together butter and sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients, except flour, cherries and pecans.
Beat until blended well.
Reduce mixer speed to low and add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, beating just until blended.
Stir in cherries and pecans.
Spread evenly in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: easy onion rings
directions: Cut onions into rings.
Dip rings into the milk, then flour. Drain flour rings on paper towel.
Beat eggs well and add 1 cup milk.
Dip rings into this mixture.
Dip rings back into flour again.
Place on paper towel to dry.
Fry 2 or 3 at a time at 375° and sprinkle with salt.
May be made 3 hours ahead.

title: mexican green beans casserole
directions: In a large skillet with a small amount of oil, combine ham, chopped onion, pepper and flour.
Heat; then add green beans, tomatoes and other ingredients.
Cook, stirring often, until beginning to thicken.
Pour into casserole.
Put into a 400° oven abut 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Grease a loaf cake pan.
Place diced rhubarb in bottom of pan. Pour 1 cup of sugar over rhubarb.
Then make batter and pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° until tests clean, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Chop 1 cup of the broccoli.
Add onion and saute at medium heat, about 5 minutes.
Put in blender and liquify; then return to pan and saute again for about 1 or 2 minutes.
Add remaining broccoli, milk and dissolved bouillon cubes.
Cook at low heat about 5 minutes, careful not to scorch.
Then thicken with cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Serve hot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain and place meat in casserole dish.
Add macaroni and tomato sauce and stir all ingredients together.
Top with cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.l

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour and soda.
Sift flour and soda together and add.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bob's slovak stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage until leaves are soft; loosen leaves.
Set aside. In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except soup.
Spoon mixture onto each large leaf (about 2 tablespoons in each).
Fold and fasten cabbage leaf with a toothpick.
Layer bottom of large pot with unused cabbage leaves.
Place stuffed cabbage leaves in layers.
Cover with soup and any remaining leaves.
Cook on high flame until bubbling.
Simmer with cover on for 2 hours.

title: mexican hot sauce
directions: Cook together until tender.
Thicken as desired.
You may also want to vary the seasonings to your taste.
Use with meat, eggs, taco salad, etc.

title: cook it all together chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in pot.
Add butter.
Let cook until chicken is done.
Remove chicken; let cool.
Remove bones.
Tear chicken into small pieces.
Put back into butter water; bring to boil.
Roll canned biscuits into small pieces.
Drop into chicken; boil about 10 minutes on high, stirring to avoid sticking.
Reduce heat and cook 15 minutes longer until it's all cooked together and dumplings are done.
Tastes great by itself or over rice.

title: nappa salad
directions: Heat to dissolve the sugar.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush and mix well Oreo cookies with melted butter.
Flatten and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cookie mixture.
Mix pudding mix (follow directions on package).
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip and some crushed Oreo cookies.
Chill at least 6 hours.

title: pork chops
directions: Spread chops
with
mustard
on
each
side.
Coat with flour. Do
not
salt.
Put
pork
chops in fairly hot skillet with a little
vegetable
oil and brown each side, turning as needed. Put
browned chops in shallow baking dish.
Pour soup over chops. Add
water
so you will have enough liquid.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread; butter and layer in 9 x 13-inch dish. Cook sausage; spoon over bread. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine eggs and half and half; pour over cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: cracker snack mix
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients. Mix oil and dressing. Mix and toss over cracker mix. Place on large pans. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: kaitlyn dip
directions: Mix together Ranch dressing, 1000 Island dressing, mustard and relish. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Serve with chips.
